9// This file implements integer type expansion and promotion for LegalizeTypes.
10// Promotion is the act of changing a computation in an illegal type into a
11// computation in a larger type. For example, implementing i8 arithmetic in an
12// i32 register (often needed on powerpc).
13// Expansion is the act of changing a computation in an illegal type into a
14// computation in two identical registers of a smaller type. For example,
15// implementing i64 arithmetic in two i32 registers (often needed on 32-bit
16// targets).
17//
18//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
19
20#include "LegalizeTypes.h"
21#include "llvm/IR/DerivedTypes.h"
22#include "llvm/Support/ErrorHandling.h"
23#include "llvm/Support/KnownBits.h"
24#include "llvm/Support/raw_ostream.h"

30// Integer Result Promotion
31//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

33/// PromoteIntegerResult - This method is called when a result of a node is
34/// found to be in need of promotion to a larger type. At this point, the node
35/// may also have invalid operands or may have other results that need
36/// expansion, we just know that (at least) one result needs promotion.
37void DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntegerResult(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
38 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Promote integer result: "; N->dump(&DAG);
39 dbgs() << "\n");
40 SDValue Res = SDValue();
41
42 // See if the target wants to custom expand this node.
43 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(ResNo), true)) {
44 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Node has been custom expanded, done\n");
45 return;
46 }
47
48 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
49 default:
50#ifndef NDEBUG
51 dbgs() << "PromoteIntegerResult #" << ResNo << ": ";
52 N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n";
53#endif
54 llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to promote this operator!");
55 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:Res = PromoteIntRes_MERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo); break;
56 case ISD::AssertSext: Res = PromoteIntRes_AssertSext(N); break;
57 case ISD::AssertZext: Res = PromoteIntRes_AssertZext(N); break;
58 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = PromoteIntRes_BITCAST(N); break;
59 case ISD::BITREVERSE: Res = PromoteIntRes_BITREVERSE(N); break;
60 case ISD::BSWAP: Res = PromoteIntRes_BSWAP(N); break;
61 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: Res = PromoteIntRes_BUILD_PAIR(N); break;
62 case ISD::Constant: Res = PromoteIntRes_Constant(N); break;
63 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
64 case ISD::CTLZ: Res = PromoteIntRes_CTLZ(N); break;
65 case ISD::CTPOP: Res = PromoteIntRes_CTPOP(N); break;
66 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
67 case ISD::CTTZ: Res = PromoteIntRes_CTTZ(N); break;
68 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
69 Res = PromoteIntRes_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
70 case ISD::LOAD: Res = PromoteIntRes_LOAD(cast<LoadSDNode>(N)); break;
71 case ISD::MLOAD: Res = PromoteIntRes_MLOAD(cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(N));
72 break;
73 case ISD::MGATHER: Res = PromoteIntRes_MGATHER(cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N));
74 break;
75 case ISD::SELECT: Res = PromoteIntRes_SELECT(N); break;
76 case ISD::VSELECT: Res = PromoteIntRes_VSELECT(N); break;
77 case ISD::SELECT_CC: Res = PromoteIntRes_SELECT_CC(N); break;
78 case ISD::SETCC: Res = PromoteIntRes_SETCC(N); break;
79 case ISD::SMIN:
80 case ISD::SMAX: Res = PromoteIntRes_SExtIntBinOp(N); break;
81 case ISD::UMIN:
82 case ISD::UMAX: Res = PromoteIntRes_ZExtIntBinOp(N); break;
83
84 case ISD::SHL: Res = PromoteIntRes_SHL(N); break;
85 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
86 Res = PromoteIntRes_SIGN_EXTEND_INREG(N); break;
87 case ISD::SRA: Res = PromoteIntRes_SRA(N); break;
88 case ISD::SRL: Res = PromoteIntRes_SRL(N); break;
89 case ISD::TRUNCATE: Res = PromoteIntRes_TRUNCATE(N); break;
90 case ISD::UNDEF: Res = PromoteIntRes_UNDEF(N); break;
91 case ISD::VAARG: Res = PromoteIntRes_VAARG(N); break;
92
93 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR:
94 Res = PromoteIntRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
95 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE:
96 Res = PromoteIntRes_VECTOR_SHUFFLE(N); break;
97 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:
98 Res = PromoteIntRes_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
99 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
100 Res = PromoteIntRes_BUILD_VECTOR(N); break;
101 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:
102 Res = PromoteIntRes_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(N); break;
103 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS:
104 Res = PromoteIntRes_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
105
106 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
107 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
108 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
109 Res = PromoteIntRes_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(N); break;
110
111 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
112 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
113 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: Res = PromoteIntRes_INT_EXTEND(N); break;
114
115 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
116 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: Res = PromoteIntRes_FP_TO_XINT(N); break;
117
118 case ISD::FP_TO_FP16: Res = PromoteIntRes_FP_TO_FP16(N); break;
119
120 case ISD::FLT_ROUNDS_: Res = PromoteIntRes_FLT_ROUNDS(N); break;
121
122 case ISD::AND:
123 case ISD::OR:
124 case ISD::XOR:
125 case ISD::ADD:
126 case ISD::SUB:
127 case ISD::MUL: Res = PromoteIntRes_SimpleIntBinOp(N); break;
128
129 case ISD::SDIV:
130 case ISD::SREM: Res = PromoteIntRes_SExtIntBinOp(N); break;
131
132 case ISD::UDIV:
133 case ISD::UREM: Res = PromoteIntRes_ZExtIntBinOp(N); break;
134
135 case ISD::SADDO:
136 case ISD::SSUBO: Res = PromoteIntRes_SADDSUBO(N, ResNo); break;
137 case ISD::UADDO:
138 case ISD::USUBO: Res = PromoteIntRes_UADDSUBO(N, ResNo); break;
139 case ISD::SMULO:
140 case ISD::UMULO: Res = PromoteIntRes_XMULO(N, ResNo); break;
141
142 case ISD::ADDE:
143 case ISD::SUBE:
144 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
145 case ISD::SUBCARRY: Res = PromoteIntRes_ADDSUBCARRY(N, ResNo); break;
146
147 case ISD::SADDSAT:
148 case ISD::UADDSAT:
149 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
150 case ISD::USUBSAT: Res = PromoteIntRes_ADDSUBSAT(N); break;
151 case ISD::SMULFIX:
152 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
153 case ISD::UMULFIX: Res = PromoteIntRes_MULFIX(N); break;
154 case ISD::ABS: Res = PromoteIntRes_ABS(N); break;
155
156 case ISD::PTRTOINT: Res = PromoteIntRes_PTRTOINT(N); break;
157
158 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD:
159 Res = PromoteIntRes_Atomic0(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)); break;
160
161 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
162 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
163 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
164 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
165 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
166 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
167 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
168 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
169 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
170 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
171 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
172 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
173 Res = PromoteIntRes_Atomic1(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)); break;
174
175 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
176 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS:
177 Res = PromoteIntRes_AtomicCmpSwap(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N), ResNo);
178 break;
179
180 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
181 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
182 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
183 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
184 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
185 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
186 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
187 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
188 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
189 Res = PromoteIntRes_VECREDUCE(N);
190 break;
191 }
192
193 // If the result is null then the sub-method took care of registering it.
194 if (Res.getNode())
195 SetPromotedInteger(SDValue(N, ResNo), Res);
196}

198SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_MERGE_VALUES(SDNode *N,
199 unsigned ResNo) {
200 SDValue Op = DisintegrateMERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo);
201 return GetPromotedInteger(Op);
202}

204SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_AssertSext(SDNode *N) {
205 // Sign-extend the new bits, and continue the assertion.
206 SDValue Op = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
207 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, SDLoc(N),
208 Op.getValueType(), Op, N->getOperand(1));
209}
210
211SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_AssertZext(SDNode *N) {
212 // Zero the new bits, and continue the assertion.
213 SDValue Op = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
214 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, SDLoc(N),
215 Op.getValueType(), Op, N->getOperand(1));
216}

218SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_Atomic0(AtomicSDNode *N) {
219 EVT ResVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
220 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomic(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
221 N->getMemoryVT(), ResVT,
222 N->getChain(), N->getBasePtr(),
223 N->getMemOperand());
224 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
225 // use the new one.
226 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
227 return Res;
228}
229
230SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_Atomic1(AtomicSDNode *N) {
231 SDValue Op2 = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(2));
232 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomic(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N),
233 N->getMemoryVT(),
234 N->getChain(), N->getBasePtr(),
235 Op2, N->getMemOperand());
236 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
237 // use the new one.
238 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
239 return Res;
240}
241
242SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_AtomicCmpSwap(AtomicSDNode *N,
243 unsigned ResNo) {
244 if (ResNo == 1) {
245 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS);
246 EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(N->getOperand(2).getValueType());
247 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(1));
248
249 // Only use the result of getSetCCResultType if it is legal,
250 // otherwise just use the promoted result type (NVT).
251 if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(SVT))
252 SVT = NVT;
253
254 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(N->getValueType(0), SVT, MVT::Other);
255 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap(
256 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS, SDLoc(N), N->getMemoryVT(), VTs,
257 N->getChain(), N->getBasePtr(), N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3),
258 N->getMemOperand());
259 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res.getValue(0));
260 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 2), Res.getValue(2));
261 return Res.getValue(1);
262 }
263
264 SDValue Op2 = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(2));
265 SDValue Op3 = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(3));
266 SDVTList VTs =
267 DAG.getVTList(Op2.getValueType(), N->getValueType(1), MVT::Other);
268 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap(
269 N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), N->getMemoryVT(), VTs, N->getChain(),
270 N->getBasePtr(), Op2, Op3, N->getMemOperand());
271 // Update the use to N with the newly created Res.
272 for (unsigned i = 1, NumResults = N->getNumValues(); i < NumResults; ++i)
273 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, i), Res.getValue(i));
274 return Res;
275}

277SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_PTRTOINT(SDNode *N) {
278 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
279 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
280 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
281 SDLoc dl(N);
282 return DAG.getNode(ISD::PTRTOINT, dl, NOutVT, InOp);
283}
284
285SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {
286 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
287 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
288 EVT NInVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT);
289 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
290 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
291 SDLoc dl(N);
292
293 switch (getTypeAction(InVT)) {
294 case TargetLowering::TypeLegal:
295 break;
296 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger:
297 if (NOutVT.bitsEq(NInVT) && !NOutVT.isVector() && !NInVT.isVector())
298 // The input promotes to the same size. Convert the promoted value.
299 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NOutVT, GetPromotedInteger(InOp));
300 break;
301 case TargetLowering::TypeSoftenFloat:
302 // Promote the integer operand by hand.
303 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVT, GetSoftenedFloat(InOp));
304 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteFloat: {
305 // Convert the promoted float by hand.
306 if (!NOutVT.isVector())
307 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_TO_FP16, dl, NOutVT, GetPromotedFloat(InOp));
308 break;
309 }
310 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger:
311 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandFloat:
312 break;
313 case TargetLowering::TypeScalarizeVector:
314 // Convert the element to an integer and promote it by hand.
315 if (!NOutVT.isVector())
316 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVT,
317 BitConvertToInteger(GetScalarizedVector(InOp)));
318 break;
319 case TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector: {
320 if (!NOutVT.isVector()) {
321 // For example, i32 = BITCAST v2i16 on alpha. Convert the split
322 // pieces of the input into integers and reassemble in the final type.
323 SDValue Lo, Hi;
324 GetSplitVector(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
325 Lo = BitConvertToInteger(Lo);
326 Hi = BitConvertToInteger(Hi);
327
328 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
329 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
330
331 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl,
332 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
333 NOutVT.getSizeInBits()),
334 JoinIntegers(Lo, Hi));
335 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NOutVT, InOp);
336 }
337 break;
338 }
339 case TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector:
340 // The input is widened to the same size. Convert to the widened value.
341 // Make sure that the outgoing value is not a vector, because this would
342 // make us bitcast between two vectors which are legalized in different ways.
343 if (NOutVT.bitsEq(NInVT) && !NOutVT.isVector())
344 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NOutVT, GetWidenedVector(InOp));
345 // If the output type is also a vector and widening it to the same size
346 // as the widened input type would be a legal type, we can widen the bitcast
347 // and handle the promotion after.
348 if (NOutVT.isVector()) {
349 unsigned WidenInSize = NInVT.getSizeInBits();
350 unsigned OutSize = OutVT.getSizeInBits();
351 if (WidenInSize % OutSize == 0) {
352 unsigned Scale = WidenInSize / OutSize;
353 EVT WideOutVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
354 OutVT.getVectorElementType(),
355 OutVT.getVectorNumElements() * Scale);
356 if (isTypeLegal(WideOutVT)) {
357 InOp = DAG.getBitcast(WideOutVT, GetWidenedVector(InOp));
358 MVT IdxTy = TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
359 InOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, OutVT, InOp,
360 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, IdxTy));
361 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVT, InOp);
362 }
363 }
364 }
365 }
366
367 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVT,
368 CreateStackStoreLoad(InOp, OutVT));
369}

371// Helper for BSWAP/BITREVERSE promotion to ensure we can fit the shift amount
372// in the VT returned by getShiftAmountTy and to return a safe VT if we can't.
373static EVT getShiftAmountTyForConstant(unsigned Val, EVT VT,
374 const TargetLowering &TLI,
375 SelectionDAG &DAG) {
376 EVT ShiftVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
377 // If the value won't fit in the prefered type, just use something safe. It
378 // will be legalized when the shift is expanded.
379 if ((Log2_32(Val) + 1) > ShiftVT.getScalarSizeInBits())
380 ShiftVT = MVT::i32;
381 return ShiftVT;
382}
383
384SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_BSWAP(SDNode *N) {
385 SDValue Op = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
386 EVT OVT = N->getValueType(0);
387 EVT NVT = Op.getValueType();
388 SDLoc dl(N);
389
390 unsigned DiffBits = NVT.getScalarSizeInBits() - OVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
391 EVT ShiftVT = getShiftAmountTyForConstant(DiffBits, NVT, TLI, DAG);
392 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, dl, NVT, Op),
393 DAG.getConstant(DiffBits, dl, ShiftVT));
394}

396SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_BITREVERSE(SDNode *N) {
397 SDValue Op = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
398 EVT OVT = N->getValueType(0);
399 EVT NVT = Op.getValueType();
400 SDLoc dl(N);
401
402 unsigned DiffBits = NVT.getScalarSizeInBits() - OVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
403 EVT ShiftVT = getShiftAmountTyForConstant(DiffBits, NVT, TLI, DAG);
404 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT,
405 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITREVERSE, dl, NVT, Op),
406 DAG.getConstant(DiffBits, dl, ShiftVT));
407}

409SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_BUILD_PAIR(SDNode *N) {
410 // The pair element type may be legal, or may not promote to the same type as
411 // the result, for example i14 = BUILD_PAIR (i7, i7). Handle all cases.
412 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(N),
413 TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),
414 N->getValueType(0)), JoinIntegers(N->getOperand(0),
415 N->getOperand(1)));
416}
417
418SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_Constant(SDNode *N) {
419 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
420 // FIXME there is no actual debug info here
421 SDLoc dl(N);
422 // Zero extend things like i1, sign extend everything else. It shouldn't
423 // matter in theory which one we pick, but this tends to give better code?
424 unsigned Opc = VT.isByteSized() ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
425 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl,
426 TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT),
427 SDValue(N, 0));
428 assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(Result) && "Didn't constant fold ext?");
429 return Result;
430}

432SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_CTLZ(SDNode *N) {
433 // Zero extend to the promoted type and do the count there.
434 SDValue Op = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
435 SDLoc dl(N);
436 EVT OVT = N->getValueType(0);
437 EVT NVT = Op.getValueType();
438 Op = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Op);
439 // Subtract off the extra leading bits in the bigger type.
440 return DAG.getNode(
441 ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, Op,
442 DAG.getConstant(NVT.getScalarSizeInBits() - OVT.getScalarSizeInBits(), dl,
443 NVT));
444}
445
446SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_CTPOP(SDNode *N) {
447 // Zero extend to the promoted type and do the count there.
448 SDValue Op = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
449 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, SDLoc(N), Op.getValueType(), Op);
450}
451
452SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_CTTZ(SDNode *N) {
453 SDValue Op = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
454 EVT OVT = N->getValueType(0);
455 EVT NVT = Op.getValueType();
456 SDLoc dl(N);
457 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ) {
458 // The count is the same in the promoted type except if the original
459 // value was zero. This can be handled by setting the bit just off
460 // the top of the original type.
461 auto TopBit = APInt::getOneBitSet(NVT.getScalarSizeInBits(),
462 OVT.getScalarSizeInBits());
463 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Op, DAG.getConstant(TopBit, dl, NVT));
464 }
465 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Op);
466}
467
468SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
469 SDLoc dl(N);
470 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
471
472 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
473 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
474
475 // If the input also needs to be promoted, do that first so we can get a
476 // get a good idea for the output type.
477 if (TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), Op0.getValueType())
478 == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
479 SDValue In = GetPromotedInteger(Op0);
480
481 // If the new type is larger than NVT, use it. We probably won't need to
482 // promote it again.
483 EVT SVT = In.getValueType().getScalarType();
484 if (SVT.bitsGE(NVT)) {
485 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, SVT, In, Op1);
486 return DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Ext, dl, NVT);
487 }
488 }
489
490 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, NVT, Op0, Op1);
491}

493SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_FP_TO_XINT(SDNode *N) {
494 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
495 unsigned NewOpc = N->getOpcode();
496 SDLoc dl(N);
497
498 // If we're promoting a UINT to a larger size and the larger FP_TO_UINT is
499 // not Legal, check to see if we can use FP_TO_SINT instead. (If both UINT
500 // and SINT conversions are Custom, there is no way to tell which is
501 // preferable. We choose SINT because that's the right thing on PPC.)
502 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_UINT &&
503 !TLI.isOperationLegal(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, NVT) &&
504 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, NVT))
505 NewOpc = ISD::FP_TO_SINT;
506
507 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(NewOpc, dl, NVT, N->getOperand(0));
508
509 // Assert that the converted value fits in the original type. If it doesn't
510 // (eg: because the value being converted is too big), then the result of the
511 // original operation was undefined anyway, so the assert is still correct.
512 //
513 // NOTE: fp-to-uint to fp-to-sint promotion guarantees zero extend. For example:
514 // before legalization: fp-to-uint16, 65534. -> 0xfffe
515 // after legalization: fp-to-sint32, 65534. -> 0x0000fffe
516 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_UINT ?
517 ISD::AssertZext : ISD::AssertSext, dl, NVT, Res,
518 DAG.getValueType(N->getValueType(0).getScalarType()));
519}

535SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_INT_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
536 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
537 SDLoc dl(N);
538
539 if (getTypeAction(N->getOperand(0).getValueType())
540 == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
541 SDValue Res = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
542 assert(Res.getValueType().bitsLE(NVT) && "Extension doesn't make sense!");
543
544 // If the result and operand types are the same after promotion, simplify
545 // to an in-register extension.
546 if (NVT == Res.getValueType()) {
547 // The high bits are not guaranteed to be anything. Insert an extend.
548 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
549 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, NVT, Res,
550 DAG.getValueType(N->getOperand(0).getValueType()));
551 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
552 return DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Res, dl,
553 N->getOperand(0).getValueType().getScalarType());
554 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND && "Unknown integer extension!");
555 return Res;
556 }
557 }
558
559 // Otherwise, just extend the original operand all the way to the larger type.
560 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, N->getOperand(0));
561}

575 return Res;
576}

610/// Promote the overflow flag of an overflowing arithmetic node.
611SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_Overflow(SDNode *N) {
612 // Change the return type of the boolean result while obeying
613 // getSetCCResultType.
614 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(1));
615 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
616 EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(VT);
617 SDValue Ops[3] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1) };
618 unsigned NumOps = N->getNumOperands();
619 assert(NumOps <= 3 && "Too many operands");
620 if (NumOps == 3)
621 Ops[2] = N->getOperand(2);
622
623 SDLoc dl(N);
624 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, SVT),
625 makeArrayRef(Ops, NumOps));
626
627 // Modified the sum result - switch anything that used the old sum to use
628 // the new one.
629 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
630
631 // Convert to the expected type.
632 return DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(Res.getValue(1), dl, NVT, VT);
633}
634
635SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_ADDSUBSAT(SDNode *N) {
636 // For promoting iN -> iM, this can be expanded by
637 // 1. ANY_EXTEND iN to iM
638 // 2. SHL by M-N
639 // 3. [US][ADD|SUB]SAT
640 // 4. L/ASHR by M-N
641 SDLoc dl(N);
642 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(0);
643 SDValue Op2 = N->getOperand(1);
644 unsigned OldBits = Op1.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
645
646 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
647 unsigned ShiftOp;
648 switch (Opcode) {
649 case ISD::SADDSAT:
650 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
651 ShiftOp = ISD::SRA;
652 break;
653 case ISD::UADDSAT:
654 case ISD::USUBSAT:
655 ShiftOp = ISD::SRL;
656 break;
657 default:
658 llvm_unreachable("Expected opcode to be signed or unsigned saturation "
659 "addition or subtraction");
660 }
661
662 SDValue Op1Promoted = GetPromotedInteger(Op1);
663 SDValue Op2Promoted = GetPromotedInteger(Op2);
664
665 EVT PromotedType = Op1Promoted.getValueType();
666 unsigned NewBits = PromotedType.getScalarSizeInBits();
667 unsigned SHLAmount = NewBits - OldBits;
668 EVT SHVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(PromotedType, DAG.getDataLayout());
669 SDValue ShiftAmount = DAG.getConstant(SHLAmount, dl, SHVT);
670 Op1Promoted =
671 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, PromotedType, Op1Promoted, ShiftAmount);
672 Op2Promoted =
673 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, PromotedType, Op2Promoted, ShiftAmount);
674
675 SDValue Result =
676 DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, PromotedType, Op1Promoted, Op2Promoted);
677 return DAG.getNode(ShiftOp, dl, PromotedType, Result, ShiftAmount);
678}
679
680SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_MULFIX(SDNode *N) {
681 // Can just promote the operands then continue with operation.
682 SDLoc dl(N);
683 SDValue Op1Promoted, Op2Promoted;
684 bool Signed =
685 N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX || N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT;
686 if (Signed) {
687 Op1Promoted = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
688 Op2Promoted = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
689 } else {
690 Op1Promoted = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
691 Op2Promoted = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
692 }
693 EVT OldType = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
694 EVT PromotedType = Op1Promoted.getValueType();
695 unsigned DiffSize =
696 PromotedType.getScalarSizeInBits() - OldType.getScalarSizeInBits();
697
698 bool Saturating = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT;
699 if (Saturating) {
700 // Promoting the operand and result values changes the saturation width,
701 // which is extends the values that we clamp to on saturation. This could be
702 // resolved by shifting one of the operands the same amount, which would
703 // also shift the result we compare against, then shifting back.
704 EVT ShiftTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(PromotedType, DAG.getDataLayout());
705 Op1Promoted = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, PromotedType, Op1Promoted,
706 DAG.getConstant(DiffSize, dl, ShiftTy));
707 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, PromotedType, Op1Promoted,
708 Op2Promoted, N->getOperand(2));
709 unsigned ShiftOp = Signed ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL;
710 return DAG.getNode(ShiftOp, dl, PromotedType, Result,
711 DAG.getConstant(DiffSize, dl, ShiftTy));
712 }
713 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, PromotedType, Op1Promoted, Op2Promoted,
714 N->getOperand(2));
715}
716
717SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_SADDSUBO(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
718 if (ResNo == 1)
719 return PromoteIntRes_Overflow(N);
720
721 // The operation overflowed iff the result in the larger type is not the
722 // sign extension of its truncation to the original type.
723 SDValue LHS = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
724 SDValue RHS = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
725 EVT OVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
726 EVT NVT = LHS.getValueType();
727 SDLoc dl(N);
728
729 // Do the arithmetic in the larger type.
730 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB;
731 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, NVT, LHS, RHS);
732
733 // Calculate the overflow flag: sign extend the arithmetic result from
734 // the original type.
735 SDValue Ofl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, NVT, Res,
736 DAG.getValueType(OVT));
737 // Overflowed if and only if this is not equal to Res.
738 Ofl = DAG.getSetCC(dl, N->getValueType(1), Ofl, Res, ISD::SETNE);
739
740 // Use the calculated overflow everywhere.
741 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ofl);
742
743 return Res;
744}

770SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
771 EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
772 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
773
774 EVT SVT = getSetCCResultType(InVT);
775
776 // If we got back a type that needs to be promoted, this likely means the
777 // the input type also needs to be promoted. So get the promoted type for
778 // the input and try the query again.
779 if (getTypeAction(SVT) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
780 if (getTypeAction(InVT) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
781 InVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), InVT);
782 SVT = getSetCCResultType(InVT);
783 } else {
784 // Input type isn't promoted, just use the default promoted type.
785 SVT = NVT;
786 }
787 }
788
789 SDLoc dl(N);
790 assert(SVT.isVector() == N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
791 "Vector compare must return a vector result!");
792
793 // Get the SETCC result using the canonical SETCC type.
794 SDValue SetCC = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, SVT, N->getOperand(0),
795 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2));
796
797 // Convert to the expected type.
798 return DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(SetCC, dl, NVT);
799}

859SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_TRUNCATE(SDNode *N) {
860 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
861 SDValue Res;
862 SDValue InOp = N->getOperand(0);
863 SDLoc dl(N);
864
865 switch (getTypeAction(InOp.getValueType())) {
866 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown type action!");
867 case TargetLowering::TypeLegal:
868 case TargetLowering::TypeExpandInteger:
869 Res = InOp;
870 break;
871 case TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger:
872 Res = GetPromotedInteger(InOp);
873 break;
874 case TargetLowering::TypeSplitVector: {
875 EVT InVT = InOp.getValueType();
876 assert(InVT.isVector() && "Cannot split scalar types");
877 unsigned NumElts = InVT.getVectorNumElements();
878 assert(NumElts == NVT.getVectorNumElements() &&
879 "Dst and Src must have the same number of elements");
880 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumElts) &&
881 "Promoted vector type must be a power of two");
882
883 SDValue EOp1, EOp2;
884 GetSplitVector(InOp, EOp1, EOp2);
885
886 EVT HalfNVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NVT.getScalarType(),
887 NumElts/2);
888 EOp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HalfNVT, EOp1);
889 EOp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, HalfNVT, EOp2);
890
891 return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, dl, NVT, EOp1, EOp2);
892 }
893 case TargetLowering::TypeWidenVector: {
894 SDValue WideInOp = GetWidenedVector(InOp);
895
896 // Truncate widened InOp.
897 unsigned NumElem = WideInOp.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
898 EVT TruncVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(),
899 N->getValueType(0).getScalarType(), NumElem);
900 SDValue WideTrunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, TruncVT, WideInOp);
901
902 // Zero extend so that the elements are of same type as those of NVT
903 EVT ExtVT = EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NVT.getVectorElementType(),
904 NumElem);
905 SDValue WideExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, ExtVT, WideTrunc);
906
907 // Extract the low NVT subvector.
908 MVT IdxTy = TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
909 SDValue ZeroIdx = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, IdxTy);
910 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, dl, NVT, WideExt, ZeroIdx);
911 }
912 }
913
914 // Truncate to NVT instead of VT
915 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, NVT, Res);
916}

918SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_UADDSUBO(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
919 if (ResNo == 1)
920 return PromoteIntRes_Overflow(N);
921
922 // The operation overflowed iff the result in the larger type is not the
923 // zero extension of its truncation to the original type.
924 SDValue LHS = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
925 SDValue RHS = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
926 EVT OVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
927 EVT NVT = LHS.getValueType();
928 SDLoc dl(N);
929
930 // Do the arithmetic in the larger type.
931 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB;
932 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, NVT, LHS, RHS);
933
934 // Calculate the overflow flag: zero extend the arithmetic result from
935 // the original type.
936 SDValue Ofl = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Res, dl, OVT.getScalarType());
937 // Overflowed if and only if this is not equal to Res.
938 Ofl = DAG.getSetCC(dl, N->getValueType(1), Ofl, Res, ISD::SETNE);
939
940 // Use the calculated overflow everywhere.
941 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ofl);
942
943 return Res;
944}
945
946// Handle promotion for the ADDE/SUBE/ADDCARRY/SUBCARRY nodes. Notice that
947// the third operand of ADDE/SUBE nodes is carry flag, which differs from
948// the ADDCARRY/SUBCARRY nodes in that the third operand is carry Boolean.
949SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_ADDSUBCARRY(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
950 if (ResNo == 1)
951 return PromoteIntRes_Overflow(N);
952
953 // We need to sign-extend the operands so the carry value computed by the
954 // wide operation will be equivalent to the carry value computed by the
955 // narrow operation.
956 // An ADDCARRY can generate carry only if any of the operands has its
957 // most significant bit set. Sign extension propagates the most significant
958 // bit into the higher bits which means the extra bit that the narrow
959 // addition would need (i.e. the carry) will be propagated through the higher
960 // bits of the wide addition.
961 // A SUBCARRY can generate borrow only if LHS < RHS and this property will be
962 // preserved by sign extension.
963 SDValue LHS = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
964 SDValue RHS = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
965
966 EVT ValueVTs[] = {LHS.getValueType(), N->getValueType(1)};
967
968 // Do the arithmetic in the wide type.
969 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), DAG.getVTList(ValueVTs),
970 LHS, RHS, N->getOperand(2));
971
972 // Update the users of the original carry/borrow value.
973 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Res.getValue(1));
974
975 return SDValue(Res.getNode(), 0);
976}

978SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_ABS(SDNode *N) {
979 SDValue Op0 = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
980 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ABS, SDLoc(N), Op0.getValueType(), Op0);
981}
982
983SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_XMULO(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
984 // Promote the overflow bit trivially.
985 if (ResNo == 1)
986 return PromoteIntRes_Overflow(N);
987
988 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0), RHS = N->getOperand(1);
989 SDLoc DL(N);
990 EVT SmallVT = LHS.getValueType();
991
992 // To determine if the result overflowed in a larger type, we extend the
993 // input to the larger type, do the multiply (checking if it overflows),
994 // then also check the high bits of the result to see if overflow happened
995 // there.
996 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULO) {
997 LHS = SExtPromotedInteger(LHS);
998 RHS = SExtPromotedInteger(RHS);
999 } else {
1000 LHS = ZExtPromotedInteger(LHS);
1001 RHS = ZExtPromotedInteger(RHS);
1002 }
1003 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(LHS.getValueType(), N->getValueType(1));
1004 SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VTs, LHS, RHS);
1005
1006 // Overflow occurred if it occurred in the larger type, or if the high part
1007 // of the result does not zero/sign-extend the low part. Check this second
1008 // possibility first.
1009 SDValue Overflow;
1010 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULO) {
1011 // Unsigned overflow occurred if the high part is non-zero.
1012 unsigned Shift = SmallVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1013 EVT ShiftTy = getShiftAmountTyForConstant(Shift, Mul.getValueType(),
1014 TLI, DAG);
1015 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, Mul.getValueType(), Mul,
1016 DAG.getConstant(Shift, DL, ShiftTy));
1017 Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(DL, N->getValueType(1), Hi,
1018 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, Hi.getValueType()),
1019 ISD::SETNE);
1020 } else {
1021 // Signed overflow occurred if the high part does not sign extend the low.
1022 SDValue SExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, DL, Mul.getValueType(),
1023 Mul, DAG.getValueType(SmallVT));
1024 Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(DL, N->getValueType(1), SExt, Mul, ISD::SETNE);
1025 }
1026
1027 // The only other way for overflow to occur is if the multiplication in the
1028 // larger type itself overflowed.
1029 Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, N->getValueType(1), Overflow,
1030 SDValue(Mul.getNode(), 1));
1031
1032 // Use the calculated overflow everywhere.
1033 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Overflow);
1034 return Mul;
1035}

1037SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_UNDEF(SDNode *N) {
1038 return DAG.getUNDEF(TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(),
1039 N->getValueType(0)));
1040}
1041
1042SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_VAARG(SDNode *N) {
1043 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); // Get the chain.
1044 SDValue Ptr = N->getOperand(1); // Get the pointer.
1045 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1046 SDLoc dl(N);
1047
1048 MVT RegVT = TLI.getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
1049 unsigned NumRegs = TLI.getNumRegisters(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
1050 // The argument is passed as NumRegs registers of type RegVT.
1051
1052 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Parts(NumRegs);
1053 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumRegs; ++i) {
1054 Parts[i] = DAG.getVAArg(RegVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, N->getOperand(2),
1055 N->getConstantOperandVal(3));
1056 Chain = Parts[i].getValue(1);
1057 }
1058
1059 // Handle endianness of the load.
1060 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1061 std::reverse(Parts.begin(), Parts.end());
1062
1063 // Assemble the parts in the promoted type.
1064 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
1065 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Parts[0]);
1066 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumRegs; ++i) {
1067 SDValue Part = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Parts[i]);
1068 // Shift it to the right position and "or" it in.
1069 Part = DAG.getNode(
1070 ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, Part,
1071 DAG.getConstant(i * RegVT.getSizeInBits(), dl,
1072 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
1073 Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Res, Part);
1074 }
1075
1076 // Modified the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
1077 // use the new one.
1078 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Chain);
1079
1080 return Res;
1081}
1082
1083//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1084// Integer Operand Promotion
1085//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1086
1087/// PromoteIntegerOperand - This method is called when the specified operand of
1088/// the specified node is found to need promotion. At this point, all of the
1089/// result types of the node are known to be legal, but other operands of the
1090/// node may need promotion or expansion as well as the specified one.
1091bool DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntegerOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
1092 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Promote integer operand: "; N->dump(&DAG);
1093 dbgs() << "\n");
1094 SDValue Res = SDValue();
1095
1096 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false)) {
1097 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Node has been custom lowered, done\n");
1098 return false;
1099 }
1100
1101 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1102 default:
1103 #ifndef NDEBUG
1104 dbgs() << "PromoteIntegerOperand Op #" << OpNo << ": ";
1105 N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n";
1106 #endif
1107 llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to promote this operator's operand!");
1108
1109 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: Res = PromoteIntOp_ANY_EXTEND(N); break;
1110 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE:
1111 Res = PromoteIntOp_ATOMIC_STORE(cast<AtomicSDNode>(N));
1112 break;
1113 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = PromoteIntOp_BITCAST(N); break;
1114 case ISD::BR_CC: Res = PromoteIntOp_BR_CC(N, OpNo); break;
1115 case ISD::BRCOND: Res = PromoteIntOp_BRCOND(N, OpNo); break;
1116 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: Res = PromoteIntOp_BUILD_PAIR(N); break;
1117 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: Res = PromoteIntOp_BUILD_VECTOR(N); break;
1118 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: Res = PromoteIntOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(N); break;
1119 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: Res = PromoteIntOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
1120 case ISD::INTTOPTR:
1121 Res = PromoteIntOp_INTTOPTR(N);break;
1122 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:
1123 Res = PromoteIntOp_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(N, OpNo);break;
1124 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:
1125 Res = PromoteIntOp_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(N); break;
1126 case ISD::VSELECT:
1127 case ISD::SELECT: Res = PromoteIntOp_SELECT(N, OpNo); break;
1128 case ISD::SELECT_CC: Res = PromoteIntOp_SELECT_CC(N, OpNo); break;
1129 case ISD::SETCC: Res = PromoteIntOp_SETCC(N, OpNo); break;
1130 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: Res = PromoteIntOp_SIGN_EXTEND(N); break;
1131 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: Res = PromoteIntOp_SINT_TO_FP(N); break;
1132 case ISD::STORE: Res = PromoteIntOp_STORE(cast<StoreSDNode>(N),
1133 OpNo); break;
1134 case ISD::MSTORE: Res = PromoteIntOp_MSTORE(cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(N),
1135 OpNo); break;
1136 case ISD::MLOAD: Res = PromoteIntOp_MLOAD(cast<MaskedLoadSDNode>(N),
1137 OpNo); break;
1138 case ISD::MGATHER: Res = PromoteIntOp_MGATHER(cast<MaskedGatherSDNode>(N),
1139 OpNo); break;
1140 case ISD::MSCATTER: Res = PromoteIntOp_MSCATTER(cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(N),
1141 OpNo); break;
1142 case ISD::TRUNCATE: Res = PromoteIntOp_TRUNCATE(N); break;
1143 case ISD::FP16_TO_FP:
1144 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: Res = PromoteIntOp_UINT_TO_FP(N); break;
1145 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: Res = PromoteIntOp_ZERO_EXTEND(N); break;
1146 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: Res = PromoteIntOp_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(N); break;
1147
1148 case ISD::SHL:
1149 case ISD::SRA:
1150 case ISD::SRL:
1151 case ISD::ROTL:
1152 case ISD::ROTR: Res = PromoteIntOp_Shift(N); break;
1153
1154 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
1155 case ISD::SUBCARRY: Res = PromoteIntOp_ADDSUBCARRY(N, OpNo); break;
1156
1157 case ISD::FRAMEADDR:
1158 case ISD::RETURNADDR: Res = PromoteIntOp_FRAMERETURNADDR(N); break;
1159
1160 case ISD::PREFETCH: Res = PromoteIntOp_PREFETCH(N, OpNo); break;
1161
1162 case ISD::SMULFIX:
1163 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
1164 case ISD::UMULFIX: Res = PromoteIntOp_MULFIX(N); break;
1165
1166 case ISD::FPOWI: Res = PromoteIntOp_FPOWI(N); break;
1167
1168 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
1169 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
1170 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
1171 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
1172 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
1173 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
1174 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
1175 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
1176 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN: Res = PromoteIntOp_VECREDUCE(N); break;
1177 }
1178
1179 // If the result is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
1180 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
1181
1182 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
1183 // core about this.
1184 if (Res.getNode() == N)
1185 return true;
1186
1187 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
1188 "Invalid operand expansion");
1189
1190 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
1191 return false;
1192}
1193
1194/// PromoteSetCCOperands - Promote the operands of a comparison. This code is
1195/// shared among BR_CC, SELECT_CC, and SETCC handlers.
1196void DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteSetCCOperands(SDValue &NewLHS,SDValue &NewRHS,
1197 ISD::CondCode CCCode) {
1198 // We have to insert explicit sign or zero extends. Note that we could
1199 // insert sign extends for ALL conditions. For those operations where either
1200 // zero or sign extension would be valid, use SExtOrZExtPromotedInteger
1201 // which will choose the cheapest for the target.
1202 switch (CCCode) {
1203 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer comparison!");
1204 case ISD::SETEQ:
1205 case ISD::SETNE: {
1206 SDValue OpL = GetPromotedInteger(NewLHS);
1207 SDValue OpR = GetPromotedInteger(NewRHS);
1208
1209 // We would prefer to promote the comparison operand with sign extension.
1210 // If the width of OpL/OpR excluding the duplicated sign bits is no greater
1211 // than the width of NewLHS/NewRH, we can avoid inserting real truncate
1212 // instruction, which is redundant eventually.
1213 unsigned OpLEffectiveBits =
1214 OpL.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(OpL) + 1;
1215 unsigned OpREffectiveBits =
1216 OpR.getScalarValueSizeInBits() - DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(OpR) + 1;
1217 if (OpLEffectiveBits <= NewLHS.getScalarValueSizeInBits() &&
1218 OpREffectiveBits <= NewRHS.getScalarValueSizeInBits()) {
1219 NewLHS = OpL;
1220 NewRHS = OpR;
1221 } else {
1222 NewLHS = SExtOrZExtPromotedInteger(NewLHS);
1223 NewRHS = SExtOrZExtPromotedInteger(NewRHS);
1224 }
1225 break;
1226 }
1227 case ISD::SETUGE:
1228 case ISD::SETUGT:
1229 case ISD::SETULE:
1230 case ISD::SETULT:
1231 NewLHS = SExtOrZExtPromotedInteger(NewLHS);
1232 NewRHS = SExtOrZExtPromotedInteger(NewRHS);
1233 break;
1234 case ISD::SETGE:
1235 case ISD::SETGT:
1236 case ISD::SETLT:
1237 case ISD::SETLE:
1238 NewLHS = SExtPromotedInteger(NewLHS);
1239 NewRHS = SExtPromotedInteger(NewRHS);
1240 break;
1241 }
1242}
1243
1244SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_ANY_EXTEND(SDNode *N) {
1245 SDValue Op = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1246 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), Op);
1247}

1251 return DAG.getAtomic(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), N->getMemoryVT(),
1252 N->getChain(), N->getBasePtr(), Op2, N->getMemOperand());

1255SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_BITCAST(SDNode *N) {

1261SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_BR_CC(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
1262 assert(OpNo == 2 && "Don't know how to promote this operand!");
1263
1264 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(2);
1265 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(3);
1266 PromoteSetCCOperands(LHS, RHS, cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->get());
1267
1268 // The chain (Op#0), CC (#1) and basic block destination (Op#4) are always
1269 // legal types.
1270 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0),
1271 N->getOperand(1), LHS, RHS, N->getOperand(4)),
1272 0);
1273}

1275SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_BRCOND(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
1276 assert(OpNo == 1 && "only know how to promote condition");
1277
1278 // Promote all the way up to the canonical SetCC type.
1279 SDValue Cond = PromoteTargetBoolean(N->getOperand(1), MVT::Other);
1280
1281 // The chain (Op#0) and basic block destination (Op#2) are always legal types.
1282 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0), Cond,
1283 N->getOperand(2)), 0);
1284}

1286SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_BUILD_PAIR(SDNode *N) {
1287 // Since the result type is legal, the operands must promote to it.
1288 EVT OVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
1289 SDValue Lo = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1290 SDValue Hi = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
1291 assert(Lo.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && "Operand over promoted?");
1292 SDLoc dl(N);
1293
1294 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, N->getValueType(0), Hi,
1295 DAG.getConstant(OVT.getSizeInBits(), dl,
1296 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
1297 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, N->getValueType(0), Lo, Hi);
1298}

1300SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_BUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
1301 // The vector type is legal but the element type is not. This implies
1302 // that the vector is a power-of-two in length and that the element
1303 // type does not have a strange size (eg: it is not i1).
1304 EVT VecVT = N->getValueType(0);
1305 unsigned NumElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
1306 assert(!((NumElts & 1) && (!TLI.isTypeLegal(VecVT))) &&
1307 "Legal vector of one illegal element?");
1308
1309 // Promote the inserted value. The type does not need to match the
1310 // vector element type. Check that any extra bits introduced will be
1311 // truncated away.
1312 assert(N->getOperand(0).getValueSizeInBits() >=
1313 N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits() &&
1314 "Type of inserted value narrower than vector element type!");
1315
1316 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> NewOps;
1317 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElts; ++i)
1318 NewOps.push_back(GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(i)));
1319
1320 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, NewOps), 0);
1321}

1324 SDValue InOp = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1325 return DAG.getNode(ISD::INTTOPTR, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), InOp);
1326}

1328SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N,
1329 unsigned OpNo) {
1330 if (OpNo == 1) {
1331 // Promote the inserted value. This is valid because the type does not
1332 // have to match the vector element type.
1333
1334 // Check that any extra bits introduced will be truncated away.
1335 assert(N->getOperand(1).getValueSizeInBits() >=
1336 N->getValueType(0).getScalarSizeInBits() &&
1337 "Type of inserted value narrower than vector element type!");
1338 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0),
1339 GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1)),
1340 N->getOperand(2)),
1341 0);
1342 }
1343
1344 assert(OpNo == 2 && "Different operand and result vector types?");
1345
1346 // Promote the index.
1347 SDValue Idx = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(N->getOperand(2), SDLoc(N),
1348 TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
1349 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0),
1350 N->getOperand(1), Idx), 0);
1351}

1360SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_SELECT(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
1361 assert(OpNo == 0 && "Only know how to promote the condition!");
1362 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(0);
1363 EVT OpTy = N->getOperand(1).getValueType();
1364
1365 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::VSELECT)
1366 if (SDValue Res = WidenVSELECTAndMask(N))
1367 return Res;
1368
1369 // Promote all the way up to the canonical SetCC type.
1370 EVT OpVT = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT ? OpTy.getScalarType() : OpTy;
1371 Cond = PromoteTargetBoolean(Cond, OpVT);
1372
1373 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, Cond, N->getOperand(1),
1374 N->getOperand(2)), 0);
1375}

1382 PromoteSetCCOperands(LHS, RHS, cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(4))->get());
1383
1384 // The CC (#4) and the possible return values (#2 and #3) have legal types.
1385 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, LHS, RHS, N->getOperand(2),
1386 N->getOperand(3), N->getOperand(4)), 0);
1387}

1430SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_MSTORE(MaskedStoreSDNode *N,
1431 unsigned OpNo) {
1432
1433 SDValue DataOp = N->getValue();
1434 EVT DataVT = DataOp.getValueType();
1435 SDValue Mask = N->getMask();
1436 SDLoc dl(N);
1437
1438 bool TruncateStore = false;
1439 if (OpNo == 3) {
1440 Mask = PromoteTargetBoolean(Mask, DataVT);
1441 // Update in place.
1442 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
1443 NewOps[3] = Mask;
1444 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, NewOps), 0);
1445 } else { // Data operand
1446 assert(OpNo == 1 && "Unexpected operand for promotion");
1447 DataOp = GetPromotedInteger(DataOp);
1448 TruncateStore = true;
1449 }
1450
1451 return DAG.getMaskedStore(N->getChain(), dl, DataOp, N->getBasePtr(), Mask,
1452 N->getMemoryVT(), N->getMemOperand(),
1453 TruncateStore, N->isCompressingStore());
1454}

1541SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_PREFETCH(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
1542 assert(OpNo > 1 && "Don't know how to promote this operand!");
1543 // Promote the rw, locality, and cache type arguments to a supported integer
1544 // width.
1545 SDValue Op2 = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(2));
1546 SDValue Op3 = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(3));
1547 SDValue Op4 = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(4));
1548 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1),
1549 Op2, Op3, Op4),
1550 0);
1551}
1552
1553SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_FPOWI(SDNode *N) {
1554 SDValue Op = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(1));
1555 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0), Op), 0);
1556}
1557
1558SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_VECREDUCE(SDNode *N) {
1559 SDLoc dl(N);
1560 SDValue Op;
1561 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1562 default: llvm_unreachable("Expected integer vector reduction");
1563 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
1564 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
1565 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
1566 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
1567 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
1568 Op = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1569 break;
1570 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
1571 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
1572 Op = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1573 break;
1574 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
1575 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
1576 Op = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
1577 break;
1578 }
1579
1580 EVT EltVT = Op.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
1581 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1582 if (VT.bitsGE(EltVT))
1583 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), VT, Op);
1584
1585 // Result size must be >= element size. If this is not the case after
1586 // promotion, also promote the result type and then truncate.
1587 SDValue Reduce = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, EltVT, Op);
1588 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, VT, Reduce);
1589}

1595/// ExpandIntegerResult - This method is called when the specified result of the
1596/// specified node is found to need expansion. At this point, the node may also
1597/// have invalid operands or may have other results that need promotion, we just
1598/// know that (at least) one result needs expansion.
1599void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntegerResult(SDNode *N, unsigned ResNo) {
1600 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expand integer result: "; N->dump(&DAG);
1601 dbgs() << "\n");
1602 SDValue Lo, Hi;
1603 Lo = Hi = SDValue();
1604
1605 // See if the target wants to custom expand this node.
1606 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getValueType(ResNo), true))
1607 return;
1608
1609 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1610 default:
1611#ifndef NDEBUG
1612 dbgs() << "ExpandIntegerResult #" << ResNo << ": ";
1613 N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n";
1614#endif
1615 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to expand the result of this "
1616 "operator!");
1617
1618 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: SplitRes_MERGE_VALUES(N, ResNo, Lo, Hi); break;
1619 case ISD::SELECT: SplitRes_SELECT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1620 case ISD::SELECT_CC: SplitRes_SELECT_CC(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1621 case ISD::UNDEF: SplitRes_UNDEF(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1622
1623 case ISD::BITCAST: ExpandRes_BITCAST(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1624 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: ExpandRes_BUILD_PAIR(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1625 case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT: ExpandRes_EXTRACT_ELEMENT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1626 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: ExpandRes_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1627 case ISD::VAARG: ExpandRes_VAARG(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1628
1629 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: ExpandIntRes_ANY_EXTEND(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1630 case ISD::AssertSext: ExpandIntRes_AssertSext(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1631 case ISD::AssertZext: ExpandIntRes_AssertZext(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1632 case ISD::BITREVERSE: ExpandIntRes_BITREVERSE(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1633 case ISD::BSWAP: ExpandIntRes_BSWAP(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1634 case ISD::Constant: ExpandIntRes_Constant(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1635 case ISD::ABS: ExpandIntRes_ABS(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1636 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
1637 case ISD::CTLZ: ExpandIntRes_CTLZ(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1638 case ISD::CTPOP: ExpandIntRes_CTPOP(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1639 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
1640 case ISD::CTTZ: ExpandIntRes_CTTZ(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1641 case ISD::FLT_ROUNDS_: ExpandIntRes_FLT_ROUNDS(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1642 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: ExpandIntRes_FP_TO_SINT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1643 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: ExpandIntRes_FP_TO_UINT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1644 case ISD::LLROUND: ExpandIntRes_LLROUND(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1645 case ISD::LLRINT: ExpandIntRes_LLRINT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1646 case ISD::LOAD: ExpandIntRes_LOAD(cast<LoadSDNode>(N), Lo, Hi); break;
1647 case ISD::MUL: ExpandIntRes_MUL(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1648 case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER: ExpandIntRes_READCYCLECOUNTER(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1649 case ISD::SDIV: ExpandIntRes_SDIV(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1650 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: ExpandIntRes_SIGN_EXTEND(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1651 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: ExpandIntRes_SIGN_EXTEND_INREG(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1652 case ISD::SREM: ExpandIntRes_SREM(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1653 case ISD::TRUNCATE: ExpandIntRes_TRUNCATE(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1654 case ISD::UDIV: ExpandIntRes_UDIV(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1655 case ISD::UREM: ExpandIntRes_UREM(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1656 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: ExpandIntRes_ZERO_EXTEND(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1657 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: ExpandIntRes_ATOMIC_LOAD(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1658
1659 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
1660 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
1661 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
1662 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
1663 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
1664 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
1665 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
1666 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
1667 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
1668 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
1669 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
1670 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
1671 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP: {
1672 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Tmp = ExpandAtomic(N);
1673 SplitInteger(Tmp.first, Lo, Hi);
1674 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Tmp.second);
1675 break;
1676 }
1677 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS: {
1678 AtomicSDNode *AN = cast<AtomicSDNode>(N);
1679 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(N->getValueType(0), MVT::Other);
1680 SDValue Tmp = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap(
1681 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, SDLoc(N), AN->getMemoryVT(), VTs,
1682 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3),
1683 AN->getMemOperand());
1684
1685 // Expanding to the strong ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP node means we can determine
1686 // success simply by comparing the loaded value against the ingoing
1687 // comparison.
1688 SDValue Success = DAG.getSetCC(SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(1), Tmp,
1689 N->getOperand(2), ISD::SETEQ);
1690
1691 SplitInteger(Tmp, Lo, Hi);
1692 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Success);
1693 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 2), Tmp.getValue(1));
1694 break;
1695 }
1696
1697 case ISD::AND:
1698 case ISD::OR:
1699 case ISD::XOR: ExpandIntRes_Logical(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1700
1701 case ISD::UMAX:
1702 case ISD::SMAX:
1703 case ISD::UMIN:
1704 case ISD::SMIN: ExpandIntRes_MINMAX(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1705
1706 case ISD::ADD:
1707 case ISD::SUB: ExpandIntRes_ADDSUB(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1708
1709 case ISD::ADDC:
1710 case ISD::SUBC: ExpandIntRes_ADDSUBC(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1711
1712 case ISD::ADDE:
1713 case ISD::SUBE: ExpandIntRes_ADDSUBE(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1714
1715 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
1716 case ISD::SUBCARRY: ExpandIntRes_ADDSUBCARRY(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1717
1718 case ISD::SHL:
1719 case ISD::SRA:
1720 case ISD::SRL: ExpandIntRes_Shift(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1721
1722 case ISD::SADDO:
1723 case ISD::SSUBO: ExpandIntRes_SADDSUBO(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1724 case ISD::UADDO:
1725 case ISD::USUBO: ExpandIntRes_UADDSUBO(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1726 case ISD::UMULO:
1727 case ISD::SMULO: ExpandIntRes_XMULO(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1728
1729 case ISD::SADDSAT:
1730 case ISD::UADDSAT:
1731 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
1732 case ISD::USUBSAT: ExpandIntRes_ADDSUBSAT(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1733
1734 case ISD::SMULFIX:
1735 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
1736 case ISD::UMULFIX: ExpandIntRes_MULFIX(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1737
1738 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
1739 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
1740 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
1741 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
1742 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
1743 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
1744 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
1745 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
1746 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN: ExpandIntRes_VECREDUCE(N, Lo, Hi); break;
1747 }
1748
1749 // If Lo/Hi is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
1750 if (Lo.getNode())
1751 SetExpandedInteger(SDValue(N, ResNo), Lo, Hi);
1752}

1754/// Lower an atomic node to the appropriate builtin call.
1755std::pair <SDValue, SDValue> DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandAtomic(SDNode *Node) {
1756 unsigned Opc = Node->getOpcode();
1757 MVT VT = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT();
1758 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getSYNC(Opc, VT);
1759 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unexpected atomic op or value type!");
1760
1761 return ExpandChainLibCall(LC, Node, false);
1762}

1764/// N is a shift by a value that needs to be expanded,
1765/// and the shift amount is a constant 'Amt'. Expand the operation.
1766void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandShiftByConstant(SDNode *N, const APInt &Amt,
1767 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1768 SDLoc DL(N);
1769 // Expand the incoming operand to be shifted, so that we have its parts
1770 SDValue InL, InH;
1771 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), InL, InH);
1772
1773 // Though Amt shouldn't usually be 0, it's possible. E.g. when legalization
1774 // splitted a vector shift, like this: <op1, op2> SHL <0, 2>.
1775 if (!Amt) {
1776 Lo = InL;
1777 Hi = InH;
1778 return;
1779 }
1780
1781 EVT NVT = InL.getValueType();
1782 unsigned VTBits = N->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits();
1783 unsigned NVTBits = NVT.getSizeInBits();
1784 EVT ShTy = N->getOperand(1).getValueType();
1785
1786 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
1787 if (Amt.ugt(VTBits)) {
1788 Lo = Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1789 } else if (Amt.ugt(NVTBits)) {
1790 Lo = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1791 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL,
1792 NVT, InL, DAG.getConstant(Amt - NVTBits, DL, ShTy));
1793 } else if (Amt == NVTBits) {
1794 Lo = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1795 Hi = InL;
1796 } else {
1797 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, NVT, InL, DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy));
1798 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, NVT,
1799 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, NVT, InH,
1800 DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy)),
1801 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, NVT, InL,
1802 DAG.getConstant(-Amt + NVTBits, DL, ShTy)));
1803 }
1804 return;
1805 }
1806
1807 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
1808 if (Amt.ugt(VTBits)) {
1809 Lo = Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1810 } else if (Amt.ugt(NVTBits)) {
1811 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL,
1812 NVT, InH, DAG.getConstant(Amt - NVTBits, DL, ShTy));
1813 Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1814 } else if (Amt == NVTBits) {
1815 Lo = InH;
1816 Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, NVT);
1817 } else {
1818 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, NVT,
1819 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, NVT, InL,
1820 DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy)),
1821 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, NVT, InH,
1822 DAG.getConstant(-Amt + NVTBits, DL, ShTy)));
1823 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, NVT, InH, DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy));
1824 }
1825 return;
1826 }
1827
1828 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && "Unknown shift!");
1829 if (Amt.ugt(VTBits)) {
1830 Hi = Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, NVT, InH,
1831 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, DL, ShTy));
1832 } else if (Amt.ugt(NVTBits)) {
1833 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, NVT, InH,
1834 DAG.getConstant(Amt - NVTBits, DL, ShTy));
1835 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, NVT, InH,
1836 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, DL, ShTy));
1837 } else if (Amt == NVTBits) {
1838 Lo = InH;
1839 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, NVT, InH,
1840 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, DL, ShTy));
1841 } else {
1842 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, NVT,
1843 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, NVT, InL,
1844 DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy)),
1845 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, NVT, InH,
1846 DAG.getConstant(-Amt + NVTBits, DL, ShTy)));
1847 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, DL, NVT, InH, DAG.getConstant(Amt, DL, ShTy));
1848 }
1849}
1850
1851/// ExpandShiftWithKnownAmountBit - Try to determine whether we can simplify
1852/// this shift based on knowledge of the high bit of the shift amount. If we
1853/// can tell this, we know that it is >= 32 or < 32, without knowing the actual
1854/// shift amount.
1855bool DAGTypeLegalizer::
1856ExpandShiftWithKnownAmountBit(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1857 SDValue Amt = N->getOperand(1);
1858 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
1859 EVT ShTy = Amt.getValueType();
1860 unsigned ShBits = ShTy.getScalarSizeInBits();
1861 unsigned NVTBits = NVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
1862 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NVTBits) &&
1863 "Expanded integer type size not a power of two!");
1864 SDLoc dl(N);
1865
1866 APInt HighBitMask = APInt::getHighBitsSet(ShBits, ShBits - Log2_32(NVTBits));
1867 KnownBits Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(N->getOperand(1));
1868
1869 // If we don't know anything about the high bits, exit.
1870 if (((Known.Zero|Known.One) & HighBitMask) == 0)
1871 return false;
1872
1873 // Get the incoming operand to be shifted.
1874 SDValue InL, InH;
1875 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), InL, InH);
1876
1877 // If we know that any of the high bits of the shift amount are one, then we
1878 // can do this as a couple of simple shifts.
1879 if (Known.One.intersects(HighBitMask)) {
1880 // Mask out the high bit, which we know is set.
1881 Amt = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, ShTy, Amt,
1882 DAG.getConstant(~HighBitMask, dl, ShTy));
1883
1884 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1885 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown shift");
1886 case ISD::SHL:
1887 Lo = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT); // Low part is zero.
1888 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InL, Amt); // High part from Lo part.
1889 return true;
1890 case ISD::SRL:
1891 Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT); // Hi part is zero.
1892 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InH, Amt); // Lo part from Hi part.
1893 return true;
1894 case ISD::SRA:
1895 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, InH, // Sign extend high part.
1896 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, dl, ShTy));
1897 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, InH, Amt); // Lo part from Hi part.
1898 return true;
1899 }
1900 }
1901
1902 // If we know that all of the high bits of the shift amount are zero, then we
1903 // can do this as a couple of simple shifts.
1904 if (HighBitMask.isSubsetOf(Known.Zero)) {
1905 // Calculate 31-x. 31 is used instead of 32 to avoid creating an undefined
1906 // shift if x is zero. We can use XOR here because x is known to be smaller
1907 // than 32.
1908 SDValue Amt2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, ShTy, Amt,
1909 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, dl, ShTy));
1910
1911 unsigned Op1, Op2;
1912 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1913 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown shift");
1914 case ISD::SHL: Op1 = ISD::SHL; Op2 = ISD::SRL; break;
1915 case ISD::SRL:
1916 case ISD::SRA: Op1 = ISD::SRL; Op2 = ISD::SHL; break;
1917 }
1918
1919 // When shifting right the arithmetic for Lo and Hi is swapped.
1920 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::SHL)
1921 std::swap(InL, InH);
1922
1923 // Use a little trick to get the bits that move from Lo to Hi. First
1924 // shift by one bit.
1925 SDValue Sh1 = DAG.getNode(Op2, dl, NVT, InL, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShTy));
1926 // Then compute the remaining shift with amount-1.
1927 SDValue Sh2 = DAG.getNode(Op2, dl, NVT, Sh1, Amt2);
1928
1929 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, InL, Amt);
1930 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, DAG.getNode(Op1, dl, NVT, InH, Amt),Sh2);
1931
1932 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::SHL)
1933 std::swap(Hi, Lo);
1934 return true;
1935 }
1936
1937 return false;
1938}
1939
1940/// ExpandShiftWithUnknownAmountBit - Fully general expansion of integer shift
1941/// of any size.
1942bool DAGTypeLegalizer::
1943ExpandShiftWithUnknownAmountBit(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
1944 SDValue Amt = N->getOperand(1);
1945 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
1946 EVT ShTy = Amt.getValueType();
1947 unsigned NVTBits = NVT.getSizeInBits();
1948 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NVTBits) &&
1949 "Expanded integer type size not a power of two!");
1950 SDLoc dl(N);
1951
1952 // Get the incoming operand to be shifted.
1953 SDValue InL, InH;
1954 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), InL, InH);
1955
1956 SDValue NVBitsNode = DAG.getConstant(NVTBits, dl, ShTy);
1957 SDValue AmtExcess = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, ShTy, Amt, NVBitsNode);
1958 SDValue AmtLack = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, ShTy, NVBitsNode, Amt);
1959 SDValue isShort = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(ShTy),
1960 Amt, NVBitsNode, ISD::SETULT);
1961 SDValue isZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(ShTy),
1962 Amt, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, ShTy),
1963 ISD::SETEQ);
1964
1965 SDValue LoS, HiS, LoL, HiL;
1966 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
1967 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown shift");
1968 case ISD::SHL:
1969 // Short: ShAmt < NVTBits
1970 LoS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InL, Amt);
1971 HiS = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT,
1972 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InH, Amt),
1973 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InL, AmtLack));
1974
1975 // Long: ShAmt >= NVTBits
1976 LoL = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT); // Lo part is zero.
1977 HiL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InL, AmtExcess); // Hi from Lo part.
1978
1979 Lo = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, LoS, LoL);
1980 Hi = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isZero, InH,
1981 DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, HiS, HiL));
1982 return true;
1983 case ISD::SRL:
1984 // Short: ShAmt < NVTBits
1985 HiS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InH, Amt);
1986 LoS = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT,
1987 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InL, Amt),
1988 // FIXME: If Amt is zero, the following shift generates an undefined result
1989 // on some architectures.
1990 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InH, AmtLack));
1991
1992 // Long: ShAmt >= NVTBits
1993 HiL = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT); // Hi part is zero.
1994 LoL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InH, AmtExcess); // Lo from Hi part.
1995
1996 Lo = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isZero, InL,
1997 DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, LoS, LoL));
1998 Hi = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, HiS, HiL);
1999 return true;
2000 case ISD::SRA:
2001 // Short: ShAmt < NVTBits
2002 HiS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, InH, Amt);
2003 LoS = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT,
2004 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, InL, Amt),
2005 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, InH, AmtLack));
2006
2007 // Long: ShAmt >= NVTBits
2008 HiL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, InH, // Sign of Hi part.
2009 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, dl, ShTy));
2010 LoL = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, InH, AmtExcess); // Lo from Hi part.
2011
2012 Lo = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isZero, InL,
2013 DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, LoS, LoL));
2014 Hi = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, isShort, HiS, HiL);
2015 return true;
2016 }
2017}
2018
2019static std::pair<ISD::CondCode, ISD::NodeType> getExpandedMinMaxOps(int Op) {
2020
2021 switch (Op) {
2022 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid min/max opcode");
2023 case ISD::SMAX:
2024 return std::make_pair(ISD::SETGT, ISD::UMAX);
2025 case ISD::UMAX:
2026 return std::make_pair(ISD::SETUGT, ISD::UMAX);
2027 case ISD::SMIN:
2028 return std::make_pair(ISD::SETLT, ISD::UMIN);
2029 case ISD::UMIN:
2030 return std::make_pair(ISD::SETULT, ISD::UMIN);
2031 }
2032}
2033
2034void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_MINMAX(SDNode *N,
2035 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2036 SDLoc DL(N);
2037 ISD::NodeType LoOpc;
2038 ISD::CondCode CondC;
2039 std::tie(CondC, LoOpc) = getExpandedMinMaxOps(N->getOpcode());
2040
2041 // Expand the subcomponents.
2042 SDValue LHSL, LHSH, RHSL, RHSH;
2043 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), LHSL, LHSH);
2044 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(1), RHSL, RHSH);
2045
2046 // Value types
2047 EVT NVT = LHSL.getValueType();
2048 EVT CCT = getSetCCResultType(NVT);
2049
2050 // Hi part is always the same op
2051 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, NVT, {LHSH, RHSH});
2052
2053 // We need to know whether to select Lo part that corresponds to 'winning'
2054 // Hi part or if Hi parts are equal.
2055 SDValue IsHiLeft = DAG.getSetCC(DL, CCT, LHSH, RHSH, CondC);
2056 SDValue IsHiEq = DAG.getSetCC(DL, CCT, LHSH, RHSH, ISD::SETEQ);
2057
2058 // Lo part corresponding to the 'winning' Hi part
2059 SDValue LoCmp = DAG.getSelect(DL, NVT, IsHiLeft, LHSL, RHSL);
2060
2061 // Recursed Lo part if Hi parts are equal, this uses unsigned version
2062 SDValue LoMinMax = DAG.getNode(LoOpc, DL, NVT, {LHSL, RHSL});
2063
2064 Lo = DAG.getSelect(DL, NVT, IsHiEq, LoMinMax, LoCmp);
2065}

2067void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_ADDSUB(SDNode *N,
2068 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2069 SDLoc dl(N);
2070 // Expand the subcomponents.
2071 SDValue LHSL, LHSH, RHSL, RHSH;
2072 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), LHSL, LHSH);
2073 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(1), RHSL, RHSH);
2074
2075 EVT NVT = LHSL.getValueType();
2076 SDValue LoOps[2] = { LHSL, RHSL };
2077 SDValue HiOps[3] = { LHSH, RHSH };
2078
2079 bool HasOpCarry = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(
2080 N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY,
2081 TLI.getTypeToExpandTo(*DAG.getContext(), NVT));
2082 if (HasOpCarry) {
2083 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(NVT, getSetCCResultType(NVT));
2084 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
2085 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::UADDO, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2086 HiOps[2] = Lo.getValue(1);
2087 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDCARRY, dl, VTList, HiOps);
2088 } else {
2089 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::USUBO, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2090 HiOps[2] = Lo.getValue(1);
2091 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBCARRY, dl, VTList, HiOps);
2092 }
2093 return;
2094 }
2095
2096 // Do not generate ADDC/ADDE or SUBC/SUBE if the target does not support
2097 // them. TODO: Teach operation legalization how to expand unsupported
2098 // ADDC/ADDE/SUBC/SUBE. The problem is that these operations generate
2099 // a carry of type MVT::Glue, but there doesn't seem to be any way to
2100 // generate a value of this type in the expanded code sequence.
2101 bool hasCarry =
2102 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD ?
2103 ISD::ADDC : ISD::SUBC,
2104 TLI.getTypeToExpandTo(*DAG.getContext(), NVT));
2105
2106 if (hasCarry) {
2107 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(NVT, MVT::Glue);
2108 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
2109 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDC, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2110 HiOps[2] = Lo.getValue(1);
2111 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDE, dl, VTList, HiOps);
2112 } else {
2113 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBC, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2114 HiOps[2] = Lo.getValue(1);
2115 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBE, dl, VTList, HiOps);
2116 }
2117 return;
2118 }
2119
2120 bool hasOVF =
2121 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD ?
2122 ISD::UADDO : ISD::USUBO,
2123 TLI.getTypeToExpandTo(*DAG.getContext(), NVT));
2124 TargetLoweringBase::BooleanContent BoolType = TLI.getBooleanContents(NVT);
2125
2126 if (hasOVF) {
2127 EVT OvfVT = getSetCCResultType(NVT);
2128 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(NVT, OvfVT);
2129 int RevOpc;
2130 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
2131 RevOpc = ISD::SUB;
2132 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::UADDO, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2133 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, makeArrayRef(HiOps, 2));
2134 } else {
2135 RevOpc = ISD::ADD;
2136 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::USUBO, dl, VTList, LoOps);
2137 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, makeArrayRef(HiOps, 2));
2138 }
2139 SDValue OVF = Lo.getValue(1);
2140
2141 switch (BoolType) {
2142 case TargetLoweringBase::UndefinedBooleanContent:
2143 OVF = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, OvfVT, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, OvfVT), OVF);
2144 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2145 case TargetLoweringBase::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
2146 OVF = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(OVF, dl, NVT);
2147 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Hi, OVF);
2148 break;
2149 case TargetLoweringBase::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
2150 OVF = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(OVF, dl, NVT);
2151 Hi = DAG.getNode(RevOpc, dl, NVT, Hi, OVF);
2152 }
2153 return;
2154 }
2155
2156 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
2157 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, LoOps);
2158 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, makeArrayRef(HiOps, 2));
2159 SDValue Cmp1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(NVT), Lo, LoOps[0],
2160 ISD::SETULT);
2161
2162 if (BoolType == TargetLoweringBase::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent) {
2163 SDValue Carry = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Cmp1, dl, NVT);
2164 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, Hi, Carry);
2165 return;
2166 }
2167
2168 SDValue Carry1 = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, Cmp1,
2169 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, NVT),
2170 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT));
2171 SDValue Cmp2 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(NVT), Lo, LoOps[1],
2172 ISD::SETULT);
2173 SDValue Carry2 = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, Cmp2,
2174 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, NVT), Carry1);
2175 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, Hi, Carry2);
2176 } else {
2177 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, LoOps);
2178 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, makeArrayRef(HiOps, 2));
2179 SDValue Cmp =
2180 DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(LoOps[0].getValueType()),
2181 LoOps[0], LoOps[1], ISD::SETULT);
2182
2183 SDValue Borrow;
2184 if (BoolType == TargetLoweringBase::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent)
2185 Borrow = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Cmp, dl, NVT);
2186 else
2187 Borrow = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, Cmp, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, NVT),
2188 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT));
2189
2190 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, Hi, Borrow);
2191 }
2192}

2240void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_UADDSUBO(SDNode *N,
2241 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2242 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
2243 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
2244 SDLoc dl(N);
2245
2246 SDValue Ovf;
2247
2248 bool HasOpCarry = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(
2249 N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY,
2250 TLI.getTypeToExpandTo(*DAG.getContext(), LHS.getValueType()));
2251
2252 if (HasOpCarry) {
2253 // Expand the subcomponents.
2254 SDValue LHSL, LHSH, RHSL, RHSH;
2255 GetExpandedInteger(LHS, LHSL, LHSH);
2256 GetExpandedInteger(RHS, RHSL, RHSH);
2257 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(LHSL.getValueType(), N->getValueType(1));
2258 SDValue LoOps[2] = { LHSL, RHSL };
2259 SDValue HiOps[3] = { LHSH, RHSH };
2260
2261 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY;
2262 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, VTList, LoOps);
2263 HiOps[2] = Lo.getValue(1);
2264 Hi = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VTList, HiOps);
2265
2266 Ovf = Hi.getValue(1);
2267 } else {
2268 // Expand the result by simply replacing it with the equivalent
2269 // non-overflow-checking operation.
2270 auto Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB;
2271 SDValue Sum = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, LHS.getValueType(), LHS, RHS);
2272 SplitInteger(Sum, Lo, Hi);
2273
2274 // Calculate the overflow: addition overflows iff a + b < a, and subtraction
2275 // overflows iff a - b > a.
2276 auto Cond = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT;
2277 Ovf = DAG.getSetCC(dl, N->getValueType(1), Sum, LHS, Cond);
2278 }
2279
2280 // Legalized the flag result - switch anything that used the old flag to
2281 // use the new one.
2282 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ovf);
2283}

2305void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_ANY_EXTEND(SDNode *N,
2306 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2307 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
2308 SDLoc dl(N);
2309 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
2310 if (Op.getValueType().bitsLE(NVT)) {
2311 // The low part is any extension of the input (which degenerates to a copy).
2312 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Op);
2313 Hi = DAG.getUNDEF(NVT); // The high part is undefined.
2314 } else {
2315 // For example, extension of an i48 to an i64. The operand type necessarily
2316 // promotes to the result type, so will end up being expanded too.
2317 assert(getTypeAction(Op.getValueType()) ==
2318 TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger &&
2319 "Only know how to promote this result!");
2320 SDValue Res = GetPromotedInteger(Op);
2321 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) &&
2322 "Operand over promoted?");
2323 // Split the promoted operand. This will simplify when it is expanded.
2324 SplitInteger(Res, Lo, Hi);
2325 }

2329 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2330 SDLoc dl(N);
2331 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
2332 EVT NVT = Lo.getValueType();

2334 unsigned NVTBits = NVT.getSizeInBits();
2335 unsigned EVTBits = EVT.getSizeInBits();
2336
2337 if (NVTBits < EVTBits) {
2338 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, dl, NVT, Hi,

2340 EVTBits - NVTBits)));

2342 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, dl, NVT, Lo, DAG.getValueType(EVT));
2343 // The high part replicates the sign bit of Lo, make it explicit.
2344 Hi = DAG.getNode(
2345 ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, Lo,
2346 DAG.getConstant(NVTBits - 1, dl,
2347 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));

2499void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_FP_TO_UINT(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
2500 SDValue &Hi) {

2504 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
2505 if (getTypeAction(Op.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteFloat)

2508 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getFPTOUINT(Op.getValueType(), VT);
2509 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unexpected fp-to-uint conversion!");
2510 SplitInteger(TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, VT, Op, false/*irrelevant*/, dl).first,
2511 Lo, Hi);
