2565
2566void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_LOAD(LoadSDNode *N,
2567 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2568 if (ISD::isNormalLoad(N)) {
2569 ExpandRes_NormalLoad(N, Lo, Hi);
2570 return;
2571 }
2572
2573 assert(ISD::isUNINDEXEDLoad(N) && "Indexed load during type legalization!");
2574
2575 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2576 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
2577 SDValue Ch = N->getChain();
2578 SDValue Ptr = N->getBasePtr();
2579 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = N->getExtensionType();
2580 unsigned Alignment = N->getAlignment();
2581 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = N->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
2582 AAMDNodes AAInfo = N->getAAInfo();
2583 SDLoc dl(N);
2584
2585 assert(NVT.isByteSized() && "Expanded type not byte sized!");
2586
2587 if (N->getMemoryVT().bitsLE(NVT)) {
2588 EVT MemVT = N->getMemoryVT();
2589
2590 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, NVT, Ch, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), MemVT,
2591 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2592
2593 // Remember the chain.
2594 Ch = Lo.getValue(1);
2595
2596 if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
2597 // The high part is obtained by SRA'ing all but one of the bits of the
2598 // lo part.
2599 unsigned LoSize = Lo.getValueSizeInBits();
2600 Hi = DAG.getNode(
2601 ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, Lo,
2602 DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
2603 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
2604 } else if (ExtType == ISD::ZEXTLOAD) {
2605 // The high part is just a zero.
2606 Hi = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT);
2607 } else {
2608 assert(ExtType == ISD::EXTLOAD && "Unknown extload!");
2609 // The high part is undefined.
2610 Hi = DAG.getUNDEF(NVT);
2611 }
2612 } else if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
2613 // Little-endian - low bits are at low addresses.
2614 Lo = DAG.getLoad(NVT, dl, Ch, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), Alignment, MMOFlags,
2615 AAInfo);
2616
2617 unsigned ExcessBits =
2618 N->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() - NVT.getSizeInBits();
2619 EVT NEVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExcessBits);
2620
2621 // Increment the pointer to the other half.
2622 unsigned IncrementSize = NVT.getSizeInBits()/8;
2623 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Ptr.getValueType(), Ptr,
2624 DAG.getConstant(IncrementSize, dl, Ptr.getValueType()));
2625 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, NVT, Ch, Ptr,
2626 N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), NEVT,
2627 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2628
2629 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
2630 // other one.
2631 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
2632 Hi.getValue(1));
2633 } else {
2634 // Big-endian - high bits are at low addresses. Favor aligned loads at
2635 // the cost of some bit-fiddling.
2636 EVT MemVT = N->getMemoryVT();
2637 unsigned EBytes = MemVT.getStoreSize();
2638 unsigned IncrementSize = NVT.getSizeInBits()/8;
2639 unsigned ExcessBits = (EBytes - IncrementSize)*8;
2640
2641 // Load both the high bits and maybe some of the low bits.
2642 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, NVT, Ch, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(),
2643 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
2644 MemVT.getSizeInBits() - ExcessBits),
2645 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2646
2647 // Increment the pointer to the other half.
2648 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
2649 // Load the rest of the low bits.
2650 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, NVT, Ch, Ptr,
2651 N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
2652 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExcessBits),
2653 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
2654
2655 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of the
2656 // other one.
2657 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
2658 Hi.getValue(1));
2659
2660 if (ExcessBits < NVT.getSizeInBits()) {
2661 // Transfer low bits from the bottom of Hi to the top of Lo.
2662 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Lo,
2663 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, Hi,
2664 DAG.getConstant(ExcessBits, dl,
2665 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(
2666 DAG.getDataLayout()))));
2667 // Move high bits to the right position in Hi.
2668 Hi = DAG.getNode(
2669 ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD ? ISD::SRA : ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, Hi,
2670 DAG.getConstant(NVT.getSizeInBits() - ExcessBits, dl,
2671 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
2672 }
2673 }
2674
2675 // Legalize the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
2676 // use the new one.
2677 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ch);
2678}

2680void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_Logical(SDNode *N,
2681 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2682 SDLoc dl(N);
2683 SDValue LL, LH, RL, RH;
2684 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), LL, LH);
2685 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(1), RL, RH);
2686 Lo = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LL.getValueType(), LL, RL);
2687 Hi = DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, LL.getValueType(), LH, RH);
2688}
2689
2690void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_MUL(SDNode *N,
2691 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2692 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2693 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
2694 SDLoc dl(N);
2695
2696 SDValue LL, LH, RL, RH;
2697 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), LL, LH);
2698 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(1), RL, RH);
2699
2700 if (TLI.expandMUL(N, Lo, Hi, NVT, DAG,
2701 TargetLowering::MulExpansionKind::OnlyLegalOrCustom,
2702 LL, LH, RL, RH))
2703 return;
2704
2705 // If nothing else, we can make a libcall.
2706 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
2707 if (VT == MVT::i16)
2708 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I16;
2709 else if (VT == MVT::i32)
2710 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I32;
2711 else if (VT == MVT::i64)
2712 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I64;
2713 else if (VT == MVT::i128)
2714 LC = RTLIB::MUL_I128;
2715
2716 if (LC == RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL || !TLI.getLibcallName(LC)) {
2717 // We'll expand the multiplication by brute force because we have no other
2718 // options. This is a trivially-generalized version of the code from
2719 // Hacker's Delight (itself derived from Knuth's Algorithm M from section
2720 // 4.3.1).
2721 unsigned Bits = NVT.getSizeInBits();
2722 unsigned HalfBits = Bits >> 1;
2723 SDValue Mask = DAG.getConstant(APInt::getLowBitsSet(Bits, HalfBits), dl,
2724 NVT);
2725 SDValue LLL = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, LL, Mask);
2726 SDValue RLL = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, RL, Mask);
2727
2728 SDValue T = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, LLL, RLL);
2729 SDValue TL = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, T, Mask);
2730
2731 EVT ShiftAmtTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(NVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
2732 if (APInt::getMaxValue(ShiftAmtTy.getSizeInBits()).ult(HalfBits)) {
2733 // The type from TLI is too small to fit the shift amount we want.
2734 // Override it with i32. The shift will have to be legalized.
2735 ShiftAmtTy = MVT::i32;
2736 }
2737 SDValue Shift = DAG.getConstant(HalfBits, dl, ShiftAmtTy);
2738 SDValue TH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, T, Shift);
2739 SDValue LLH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, LL, Shift);
2740 SDValue RLH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, RL, Shift);
2741
2742 SDValue U = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT,
2743 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, LLH, RLL), TH);
2744 SDValue UL = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, NVT, U, Mask);
2745 SDValue UH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, U, Shift);
2746
2747 SDValue V = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT,
2748 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, LLL, RLH), UL);
2749 SDValue VH = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, V, Shift);
2750
2751 SDValue W = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT,
2752 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, LLH, RLH),
2753 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, UH, VH));
2754 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, TL,
2755 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, V, Shift));
2756
2757 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT, W,
2758 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, NVT,
2759 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, RH, LL),
2760 DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, RL, LH)));
2761 return;
2762 }
2763
2764 SDValue Ops[2] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1) };
2765 SplitInteger(TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, VT, Ops, true/*irrelevant*/, dl).first,
2766 Lo, Hi);
2767}

2769void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_READCYCLECOUNTER(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
2770 SDValue &Hi) {
2771 SDLoc DL(N);
2772 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));

2779
2780void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_ADDSUBSAT(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
2781 SDValue &Hi) {
2782 SDValue Result = TLI.expandAddSubSat(N, DAG);
2783 SplitInteger(Result, Lo, Hi);
2784}
2785
2786/// This performs an expansion of the integer result for a fixed point
2787/// multiplication. The default expansion performs rounding down towards
2788/// negative infinity, though targets that do care about rounding should specify
2789/// a target hook for rounding and provide their own expansion or lowering of
2790/// fixed point multiplication to be consistent with rounding.
2791void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_MULFIX(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo,
2792 SDValue &Hi) {
2793 SDLoc dl(N);
2794 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2795 unsigned VTSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2796 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
2797 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
2798 uint64_t Scale = N->getConstantOperandVal(2);
2799 bool Saturating = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT;
2800 EVT BoolVT =
2801 TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
2802 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
2803 if (!Scale) {
2804 SDValue Result;
2805 if (!Saturating) {
2806 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
2807 } else {
2808 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SMULO, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, BoolVT), LHS, RHS);
2809 SDValue Product = Result.getValue(0);
2810 SDValue Overflow = Result.getValue(1);
2811
2812 APInt MinVal = APInt::getSignedMinValue(VTSize);
2813 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(VTSize);
2814 SDValue SatMin = DAG.getConstant(MinVal, dl, VT);
2815 SDValue SatMax = DAG.getConstant(MaxVal, dl, VT);
2816 SDValue ProdNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolVT, Product, Zero, ISD::SETLT);
2817 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, ProdNeg, SatMax, SatMin);
2818 Result = DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Overflow, Result, Product);
2819 }
2820 SplitInteger(Result, Lo, Hi);
2821 return;
2822 }
2823
2824 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
2825 SDValue LL, LH, RL, RH;
2826 GetExpandedInteger(LHS, LL, LH);
2827 GetExpandedInteger(RHS, RL, RH);
2828 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Result;
2829
2830 bool Signed = (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIX ||
2831 N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMULFIXSAT);
2832 unsigned LoHiOp = Signed ? ISD::SMUL_LOHI : ISD::UMUL_LOHI;
2833 if (!TLI.expandMUL_LOHI(LoHiOp, VT, dl, LHS, RHS, Result, NVT, DAG,
2834 TargetLowering::MulExpansionKind::OnlyLegalOrCustom,
2835 LL, LH, RL, RH)) {
2836 report_fatal_error("Unable to expand MUL_FIX using MUL_LOHI.");
2837 return;
2838 }
2839
2840 unsigned NVTSize = NVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2841 assert((VTSize == NVTSize * 2) && "Expected the new value type to be half "
2842 "the size of the current value type");
2843 EVT ShiftTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(NVT, DAG.getDataLayout());
2844
2845 // Shift whole amount by scale.
2846 SDValue ResultLL = Result[0];
2847 SDValue ResultLH = Result[1];
2848 SDValue ResultHL = Result[2];
2849 SDValue ResultHH = Result[3];
2850
2851 SDValue SatMax, SatMin;
2852 SDValue NVTZero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NVT);
2853 SDValue NVTNeg1 = DAG.getConstant(-1, dl, NVT);
2854 EVT BoolNVT =
2855 TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), NVT);
2856
2857 // After getting the multplication result in 4 parts, we need to perform a
2858 // shift right by the amount of the scale to get the result in that scale.
2859 // Let's say we multiply 2 64 bit numbers. The resulting value can be held in
2860 // 128 bits that are cut into 4 32-bit parts:
2861 //
2862 // HH HL LH LL
2863 // |---32---|---32---|---32---|---32---|
2864 // 128 96 64 32 0
2865 //
2866 // |------VTSize-----|
2867 //
2868 // |NVTSize-|
2869 //
2870 // The resulting Lo and Hi will only need to be one of these 32-bit parts
2871 // after shifting.
2872 if (Scale < NVTSize) {
2873 // If the scale is less than the size of the VT we expand to, the Hi and
2874 // Lo of the result will be in the first 2 parts of the result after
2875 // shifting right. This only requires shifting by the scale as far as the
2876 // third part in the result (ResultHL).
2877 SDValue SRLAmnt = DAG.getConstant(Scale, dl, ShiftTy);
2878 SDValue SHLAmnt = DAG.getConstant(NVTSize - Scale, dl, ShiftTy);
2879 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, ResultLL, SRLAmnt);
2880 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Lo,
2881 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, ResultLH, SHLAmnt));
2882 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, ResultLH, SRLAmnt);
2883 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Hi,
2884 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, ResultHL, SHLAmnt));
2885
2886 // We cannot overflow past HH when multiplying 2 ints of size VTSize, so the
2887 // highest bit of HH determines saturation direction in the event of
2888 // saturation.
2889 // The number of overflow bits we can check are VTSize - Scale + 1 (we
2890 // include the sign bit). If these top bits are > 0, then we overflowed past
2891 // the max value. If these top bits are < -1, then we overflowed past the
2892 // min value. Otherwise, we did not overflow.
2893 if (Saturating) {
2894 unsigned OverflowBits = VTSize - Scale + 1;
2895 assert(OverflowBits <= VTSize && OverflowBits > NVTSize &&
2896 "Extent of overflow bits must start within HL");
2897 SDValue HLHiMask = DAG.getConstant(
2898 APInt::getHighBitsSet(NVTSize, OverflowBits - NVTSize), dl, NVT);
2899 SDValue HLLoMask = DAG.getConstant(
2900 APInt::getLowBitsSet(NVTSize, VTSize - OverflowBits), dl, NVT);
2901
2902 // HH > 0 or HH == 0 && HL > HLLoMask
2903 SDValue HHPos = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTZero, ISD::SETGT);
2904 SDValue HHZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTZero, ISD::SETEQ);
2905 SDValue HLPos =
2906 DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHL, HLLoMask, ISD::SETUGT);
2907 SatMax = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BoolNVT, HHPos,
2908 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BoolNVT, HHZero, HLPos));
2909
2910 // HH < -1 or HH == -1 && HL < HLHiMask
2911 SDValue HHNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTNeg1, ISD::SETLT);
2912 SDValue HHNeg1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTNeg1, ISD::SETEQ);
2913 SDValue HLNeg =
2914 DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHL, HLHiMask, ISD::SETULT);
2915 SatMin = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BoolNVT, HHNeg,
2916 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BoolNVT, HHNeg1, HLNeg));
2917 }
2918 } else if (Scale == NVTSize) {
2919 // If the scales are equal, Lo and Hi are ResultLH and Result HL,
2920 // respectively. Avoid shifting to prevent undefined behavior.
2921 Lo = ResultLH;
2922 Hi = ResultHL;
2923
2924 // We overflow max if HH > 0 or HH == 0 && HL sign is negative.
2925 // We overflow min if HH < -1 or HH == -1 && HL sign is 0.
2926 if (Saturating) {
2927 SDValue HHPos = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTZero, ISD::SETGT);
2928 SDValue HHZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTZero, ISD::SETEQ);
2929 SDValue HLNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHL, NVTZero, ISD::SETLT);
2930 SatMax = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BoolNVT, HHPos,
2931 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BoolNVT, HHZero, HLNeg));
2932
2933 SDValue HHNeg = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTNeg1, ISD::SETLT);
2934 SDValue HHNeg1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, NVTNeg1, ISD::SETEQ);
2935 SDValue HLPos = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHL, NVTZero, ISD::SETGT);
2936 SatMin = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BoolNVT, HHNeg,
2937 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BoolNVT, HHNeg1, HLPos));
2938 }
2939 } else if (Scale < VTSize) {
2940 // If the scale is instead less than the old VT size, but greater than or
2941 // equal to the expanded VT size, the first part of the result (ResultLL) is
2942 // no longer a part of Lo because it would be scaled out anyway. Instead we
2943 // can start shifting right from the fourth part (ResultHH) to the second
2944 // part (ResultLH), and Result LH will be the new Lo.
2945 SDValue SRLAmnt = DAG.getConstant(Scale - NVTSize, dl, ShiftTy);
2946 SDValue SHLAmnt = DAG.getConstant(VTSize - Scale, dl, ShiftTy);
2947 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, ResultLH, SRLAmnt);
2948 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Lo,
2949 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, ResultHL, SHLAmnt));
2950 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, ResultHL, SRLAmnt);
2951 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Hi,
2952 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, ResultHH, SHLAmnt));
2953
2954 // This is similar to the case when we saturate if Scale < NVTSize, but we
2955 // only need to chech HH.
2956 if (Saturating) {
2957 unsigned OverflowBits = VTSize - Scale + 1;
2958 SDValue HHHiMask = DAG.getConstant(
2959 APInt::getHighBitsSet(NVTSize, OverflowBits), dl, NVT);
2960 SDValue HHLoMask = DAG.getConstant(
2961 APInt::getLowBitsSet(NVTSize, NVTSize - OverflowBits), dl, NVT);
2962
2963 SatMax = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, HHLoMask, ISD::SETGT);
2964 SatMin = DAG.getSetCC(dl, BoolNVT, ResultHH, HHHiMask, ISD::SETLT);
2965 }
2966 } else if (Scale == VTSize) {
2967 assert(
2968 !Signed &&
2969 "Only unsigned types can have a scale equal to the operand bit width");
2970
2971 Lo = ResultHL;
2972 Hi = ResultHH;
2973 } else {
2974 llvm_unreachable("Expected the scale to be less than or equal to the width "
2975 "of the operands");
2976 }
2977
2978 if (Saturating) {
2979 APInt LHMax = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(NVTSize);
2980 APInt LLMax = APInt::getAllOnesValue(NVTSize);
2981 APInt LHMin = APInt::getSignedMinValue(NVTSize);
2982 Hi = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, SatMax, DAG.getConstant(LHMax, dl, NVT), Hi);
2983 Hi = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, SatMin, DAG.getConstant(LHMin, dl, NVT), Hi);
2984 Lo = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, SatMax, DAG.getConstant(LLMax, dl, NVT), Lo);
2985 Lo = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, SatMin, NVTZero, Lo);
2986 }
2987}
2988
2989void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_SADDSUBO(SDNode *Node,
2990 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
2991 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
2992 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
2993 SDLoc dl(Node);
2994
2995 // Expand the result by simply replacing it with the equivalent
2996 // non-overflow-checking operation.
2997 SDValue Sum = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO ?
2998 ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB, dl, LHS.getValueType(),
2999 LHS, RHS);
3000 SplitInteger(Sum, Lo, Hi);
3001
3002 // Compute the overflow.
3003 //
3004 // LHSSign -> LHS >= 0
3005 // RHSSign -> RHS >= 0
3006 // SumSign -> Sum >= 0
3007 //
3008 // Add:
3009 // Overflow -> (LHSSign == RHSSign) && (LHSSign != SumSign)
3010 // Sub:
3011 // Overflow -> (LHSSign != RHSSign) && (LHSSign != SumSign)
3012 //
3013 EVT OType = Node->getValueType(1);
3014 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, LHS.getValueType());
3015
3016 SDValue LHSSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHS, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
3017 SDValue RHSSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, RHS, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
3018 SDValue SignsMatch = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHSSign, RHSSign,
3019 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SADDO ?
3020 ISD::SETEQ : ISD::SETNE);
3021
3022 SDValue SumSign = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, Sum, Zero, ISD::SETGE);
3023 SDValue SumSignNE = DAG.getSetCC(dl, OType, LHSSign, SumSign, ISD::SETNE);
3024
3025 SDValue Cmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, OType, SignsMatch, SumSignNE);
3026
3027 // Use the calculated overflow everywhere.
3028 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), Cmp);
3029}

3056
3057void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_Shift(SDNode *N,
3058 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
3059 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3060 SDLoc dl(N);
3061
3062 // If we can emit an efficient shift operation, do so now. Check to see if
3063 // the RHS is a constant.
3064 if (ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1)))
3065 return ExpandShiftByConstant(N, CN->getAPIntValue(), Lo, Hi);
3066
3067 // If we can determine that the high bit of the shift is zero or one, even if
3068 // the low bits are variable, emit this shift in an optimized form.
3069 if (ExpandShiftWithKnownAmountBit(N, Lo, Hi))
3070 return;
3071
3072 // If this target supports shift_PARTS, use it. First, map to the _PARTS opc.
3073 unsigned PartsOpc;
3074 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
3075 PartsOpc = ISD::SHL_PARTS;
3076 } else if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
3077 PartsOpc = ISD::SRL_PARTS;
3078 } else {
3079 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && "Unknown shift!");
3080 PartsOpc = ISD::SRA_PARTS;
3081 }
3082
3083 // Next check to see if the target supports this SHL_PARTS operation or if it
3084 // will custom expand it. Don't lower this to SHL_PARTS when we optimise for
3085 // size, but create a libcall instead.
3086 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
3087 TargetLowering::LegalizeAction Action = TLI.getOperationAction(PartsOpc, NVT);
3088 const bool LegalOrCustom =
3089 (Action == TargetLowering::Legal && TLI.isTypeLegal(NVT)) ||
3090 Action == TargetLowering::Custom;
3091
3092 if (LegalOrCustom && TLI.shouldExpandShift(DAG, N)) {
3093 // Expand the subcomponents.
3094 SDValue LHSL, LHSH;
3095 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), LHSL, LHSH);
3096 EVT VT = LHSL.getValueType();
3097
3098 // If the shift amount operand is coming from a vector legalization it may
3099 // have an illegal type. Fix that first by casting the operand, otherwise
3100 // the new SHL_PARTS operation would need further legalization.
3101 SDValue ShiftOp = N->getOperand(1);
3102 EVT ShiftTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
3103 assert(ShiftTy.getScalarSizeInBits() >=
3104 Log2_32_Ceil(VT.getScalarSizeInBits()) &&
3105 "ShiftAmountTy is too small to cover the range of this type!");
3106 if (ShiftOp.getValueType() != ShiftTy)
3107 ShiftOp = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(ShiftOp, dl, ShiftTy);
3108
3109 SDValue Ops[] = { LHSL, LHSH, ShiftOp };
3110 Lo = DAG.getNode(PartsOpc, dl, DAG.getVTList(VT, VT), Ops);
3111 Hi = Lo.getValue(1);
3112 return;
3113 }
3114
3115 // Otherwise, emit a libcall.
3116 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
3117 bool isSigned;
3118 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
3119 isSigned = false; /*sign irrelevant*/
3120 if (VT == MVT::i16)
3121 LC = RTLIB::SHL_I16;
3122 else if (VT == MVT::i32)
3123 LC = RTLIB::SHL_I32;
3124 else if (VT == MVT::i64)
3125 LC = RTLIB::SHL_I64;
3126 else if (VT == MVT::i128)
3127 LC = RTLIB::SHL_I128;
3128 } else if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
3129 isSigned = false;
3130 if (VT == MVT::i16)
3131 LC = RTLIB::SRL_I16;
3132 else if (VT == MVT::i32)
3133 LC = RTLIB::SRL_I32;
3134 else if (VT == MVT::i64)
3135 LC = RTLIB::SRL_I64;
3136 else if (VT == MVT::i128)
3137 LC = RTLIB::SRL_I128;
3138 } else {
3139 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA && "Unknown shift!");
3140 isSigned = true;
3141 if (VT == MVT::i16)
3142 LC = RTLIB::SRA_I16;
3143 else if (VT == MVT::i32)
3144 LC = RTLIB::SRA_I32;
3145 else if (VT == MVT::i64)
3146 LC = RTLIB::SRA_I64;
3147 else if (VT == MVT::i128)
3148 LC = RTLIB::SRA_I128;
3149 }
3150
3151 if (LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && TLI.getLibcallName(LC)) {
3152 SDValue Ops[2] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1) };
3153 SplitInteger(TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, VT, Ops, isSigned, dl).first, Lo, Hi);
3154 return;
3155 }
3156
3157 if (!ExpandShiftWithUnknownAmountBit(N, Lo, Hi))
3158 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported shift!");
3159}

3161void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_SIGN_EXTEND(SDNode *N,
3162 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
3163 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), N->getValueType(0));
3164 SDLoc dl(N);
3165 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
3166 if (Op.getValueType().bitsLE(NVT)) {
3167 // The low part is sign extension of the input (degenerates to a copy).
3168 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, dl, NVT, N->getOperand(0));
3169 // The high part is obtained by SRA'ing all but one of the bits of low part.
3170 unsigned LoSize = NVT.getSizeInBits();
3171 Hi = DAG.getNode(
3172 ISD::SRA, dl, NVT, Lo,
3173 DAG.getConstant(LoSize - 1, dl,
3174 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
3175 } else {
3176 // For example, extension of an i48 to an i64. The operand type necessarily
3177 // promotes to the result type, so will end up being expanded too.
3178 assert(getTypeAction(Op.getValueType()) ==
3179 TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger &&
3180 "Only know how to promote this result!");
3181 SDValue Res = GetPromotedInteger(Op);
3182 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) &&
3183 "Operand over promoted?");
3184 // Split the promoted operand. This will simplify when it is expanded.
3185 SplitInteger(Res, Lo, Hi);
3186 unsigned ExcessBits = Op.getValueSizeInBits() - NVT.getSizeInBits();
3187 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Hi,
3188 DAG.getValueType(EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
3189 ExcessBits)));
3190 }
3191}

3193void DAGTypeLegalizer::
3194ExpandIntRes_SIGN_EXTEND_INREG(SDNode *N, SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
3195 SDLoc dl(N);
3196 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
3197 EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT();
3198
3199 if (EVT.bitsLE(Lo.getValueType())) {
3200 // sext_inreg the low part if needed.
3201 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, Lo.getValueType(), Lo,
3202 N->getOperand(1));
3203
3204 // The high part gets the sign extension from the lo-part. This handles
3205 // things like sextinreg V:i64 from i8.
3206 Hi = DAG.getNode(
3207 ISD::SRA, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Lo,
3208 DAG.getConstant(Hi.getValueSizeInBits() - 1, dl,
3209 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
3210 } else {
3211 // For example, extension of an i48 to an i64. Leave the low part alone,
3212 // sext_inreg the high part.
3213 unsigned ExcessBits = EVT.getSizeInBits() - Lo.getValueSizeInBits();
3214 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Hi,
3215 DAG.getValueType(EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
3216 ExcessBits)));
3217 }
3218}

3258void DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_XMULO(SDNode *N,
3259 SDValue &Lo, SDValue &Hi) {
3260 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3261 SDLoc dl(N);
3262
3263 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::UMULO) {
3264 // This section expands the operation into the following sequence of
3265 // instructions. `iNh` here refers to a type which has half the bit width of
3266 // the type the original operation operated on.
3267 //
3268 // %0 = %LHS.HI != 0 && %RHS.HI != 0
3269 // %1 = { iNh, i1 } @umul.with.overflow.iNh(iNh %LHS.HI, iNh %RHS.LO)
3270 // %2 = { iNh, i1 } @umul.with.overflow.iNh(iNh %RHS.HI, iNh %LHS.LO)
3271 // %3 = mul nuw iN (%LHS.LOW as iN), (%RHS.LOW as iN)
3272 // %4 = add iN (%1.0 as iN) << Nh, (%2.0 as iN) << Nh
3273 // %5 = { iN, i1 } @uadd.with.overflow.iN( %4, %3 )
3274 //
3275 // %res = { %5.0, %0 || %1.1 || %2.1 || %5.1 }
3276 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0), RHS = N->getOperand(1);
3277 SDValue LHSHigh, LHSLow, RHSHigh, RHSLow;
3278 SplitInteger(LHS, LHSLow, LHSHigh);
3279 SplitInteger(RHS, RHSLow, RHSHigh);
3280 EVT HalfVT = LHSLow.getValueType()
3281 , BitVT = N->getValueType(1);
3282 SDVTList VTHalfMulO = DAG.getVTList(HalfVT, BitVT);
3283 SDVTList VTFullAddO = DAG.getVTList(VT, BitVT);
3284
3285 SDValue HalfZero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, HalfVT);
3286 SDValue Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, BitVT,
3287 DAG.getSetCC(dl, BitVT, LHSHigh, HalfZero, ISD::SETNE),
3288 DAG.getSetCC(dl, BitVT, RHSHigh, HalfZero, ISD::SETNE));
3289
3290 SDValue One = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMULO, dl, VTHalfMulO, LHSHigh, RHSLow);
3291 Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BitVT, Overflow, One.getValue(1));
3292 SDValue OneInHigh = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, VT, HalfZero,
3293 One.getValue(0));
3294
3295 SDValue Two = DAG.getNode(ISD::UMULO, dl, VTHalfMulO, RHSHigh, LHSLow);
3296 Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BitVT, Overflow, Two.getValue(1));
3297 SDValue TwoInHigh = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, dl, VT, HalfZero,
3298 Two.getValue(0));
3299
3300 // Cannot use `UMUL_LOHI` directly, because some 32-bit targets (ARM) do not
3301 // know how to expand `i64,i64 = umul_lohi a, b` and abort (why isn’t this
3302 // operation recursively legalized?).
3303 //
3304 // Many backends understand this pattern and will convert into LOHI
3305 // themselves, if applicable.
3306 SDValue Three = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT,
3307 DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, LHSLow),
3308 DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, RHSLow));
3309 SDValue Four = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, OneInHigh, TwoInHigh);
3310 SDValue Five = DAG.getNode(ISD::UADDO, dl, VTFullAddO, Three, Four);
3311 Overflow = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, BitVT, Overflow, Five.getValue(1));
3312 SplitInteger(Five, Lo, Hi);
3313 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Overflow);
3314 return;
3315 }
3316
3317 Type *RetTy = VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
3318 EVT PtrRangeVT = TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
3319 Type *PtrTy = PtrRangeVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
3320
3321 // Replace this with a libcall that will check overflow.
3322 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL;
3323 if (VT == MVT::i32)
3324 LC = RTLIB::MULO_I32;
3325 else if (VT == MVT::i64)
3326 LC = RTLIB::MULO_I64;
3327 else if (VT == MVT::i128)
3328 LC = RTLIB::MULO_I128;
3329 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unsupported XMULO!");
3330
3331 SDValue Temp = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(PtrRangeVT);
3332 // Temporary for the overflow value, default it to zero.
3333 SDValue Chain =
3334 DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, PtrRangeVT),
3335 Temp, MachinePointerInfo());
3336
3337 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
3338 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
3339 for (const SDValue &Op : N->op_values()) {
3340 EVT ArgVT = Op.getValueType();
3341 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
3342 Entry.Node = Op;
3343 Entry.Ty = ArgTy;
3344 Entry.IsSExt = true;
3345 Entry.IsZExt = false;
3346 Args.push_back(Entry);
3347 }
3348
3349 // Also pass the address of the overflow check.
3350 Entry.Node = Temp;
3351 Entry.Ty = PtrTy->getPointerTo();
3352 Entry.IsSExt = true;
3353 Entry.IsZExt = false;
3354 Args.push_back(Entry);
3355
3356 SDValue Func = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC));
3357
3358 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
3359 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
3360 .setChain(Chain)
3361 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Func, std::move(Args))
3362 .setSExtResult();
3363
3364 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
3365
3366 SplitInteger(CallInfo.first, Lo, Hi);
3367 SDValue Temp2 =
3368 DAG.getLoad(PtrRangeVT, dl, CallInfo.second, Temp, MachinePointerInfo());
3369 SDValue Ofl = DAG.getSetCC(dl, N->getValueType(1), Temp2,
3370 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, PtrRangeVT), ISD::SETNE);
3371 // Use the overflow from the libcall everywhere.
3372 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 1), Ofl);
3373}

3474 SplitInteger(Res, Lo, Hi);

3476
3477//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3478// Integer Operand Expansion
3479//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3480
3481/// ExpandIntegerOperand - This method is called when the specified operand of
3482/// the specified node is found to need expansion. At this point, all of the
3483/// result types of the node are known to be legal, but other operands of the
3484/// node may need promotion or expansion as well as the specified one.
3485bool DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntegerOperand(SDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
3486 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expand integer operand: "; N->dump(&DAG);
3487 dbgs() << "\n");
3488 SDValue Res = SDValue();
3489
3490 if (CustomLowerNode(N, N->getOperand(OpNo).getValueType(), false))
3491 return false;
3492
3493 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
3494 default:
3495 #ifndef NDEBUG
3496 dbgs() << "ExpandIntegerOperand Op #" << OpNo << ": ";
3497 N->dump(&DAG); dbgs() << "\n";
3498 #endif
3499 report_fatal_error("Do not know how to expand this operator's operand!");
3500
3501 case ISD::BITCAST: Res = ExpandOp_BITCAST(N); break;
3502 case ISD::BR_CC: Res = ExpandIntOp_BR_CC(N); break;
3503 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: Res = ExpandOp_BUILD_VECTOR(N); break;
3504 case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT: Res = ExpandOp_EXTRACT_ELEMENT(N); break;
3505 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: Res = ExpandOp_INSERT_VECTOR_ELT(N); break;
3506 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: Res = ExpandOp_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(N); break;
3507 case ISD::SELECT_CC: Res = ExpandIntOp_SELECT_CC(N); break;
3508 case ISD::SETCC: Res = ExpandIntOp_SETCC(N); break;
3509 case ISD::SETCCCARRY: Res = ExpandIntOp_SETCCCARRY(N); break;
3510 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: Res = ExpandIntOp_SINT_TO_FP(N); break;
3511 case ISD::STORE: Res = ExpandIntOp_STORE(cast<StoreSDNode>(N), OpNo); break;
3512 case ISD::TRUNCATE: Res = ExpandIntOp_TRUNCATE(N); break;
3513 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: Res = ExpandIntOp_UINT_TO_FP(N); break;
3514
3515 case ISD::SHL:
3516 case ISD::SRA:
3517 case ISD::SRL:
3518 case ISD::ROTL:
3519 case ISD::ROTR: Res = ExpandIntOp_Shift(N); break;
3520 case ISD::RETURNADDR:
3521 case ISD::FRAMEADDR: Res = ExpandIntOp_RETURNADDR(N); break;
3522
3523 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE: Res = ExpandIntOp_ATOMIC_STORE(N); break;
3524 }
3525
3526 // If the result is null, the sub-method took care of registering results etc.
3527 if (!Res.getNode()) return false;
3528
3529 // If the result is N, the sub-method updated N in place. Tell the legalizer
3530 // core about this.
3531 if (Res.getNode() == N)
3532 return true;
3533
3534 assert(Res.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) && N->getNumValues() == 1 &&
3535 "Invalid operand expansion");
3536
3537 ReplaceValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Res);
3538 return false;
3539}

3541/// IntegerExpandSetCCOperands - Expand the operands of a comparison. This code
3542/// is shared among BR_CC, SELECT_CC, and SETCC handlers.
3543void DAGTypeLegalizer::IntegerExpandSetCCOperands(SDValue &NewLHS,
3544 SDValue &NewRHS,
3545 ISD::CondCode &CCCode,
3546 const SDLoc &dl) {
3547 SDValue LHSLo, LHSHi, RHSLo, RHSHi;
3548 GetExpandedInteger(NewLHS, LHSLo, LHSHi);
3549 GetExpandedInteger(NewRHS, RHSLo, RHSHi);
3550
3551 if (CCCode == ISD::SETEQ || CCCode == ISD::SETNE) {
3552 if (RHSLo == RHSHi) {
3553 if (ConstantSDNode *RHSCST = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHSLo)) {
3554 if (RHSCST->isAllOnesValue()) {
3555 // Equality comparison to -1.
3556 NewLHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl,
3557 LHSLo.getValueType(), LHSLo, LHSHi);
3558 NewRHS = RHSLo;
3559 return;
3560 }
3561 }
3562 }
3563
3564 NewLHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, LHSLo.getValueType(), LHSLo, RHSLo);
3565 NewRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, LHSLo.getValueType(), LHSHi, RHSHi);
3566 NewLHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NewLHS.getValueType(), NewLHS, NewRHS);
3567 NewRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, NewLHS.getValueType());
3568 return;
3569 }
3570
3571 // If this is a comparison of the sign bit, just look at the top part.
3572 // X > -1, x < 0
3573 if (ConstantSDNode *CST = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(NewRHS))
3574 if ((CCCode == ISD::SETLT && CST->isNullValue()) || // X < 0
3575 (CCCode == ISD::SETGT && CST->isAllOnesValue())) { // X > -1
3576 NewLHS = LHSHi;
3577 NewRHS = RHSHi;
3578 return;
3579 }
3580
3581 // FIXME: This generated code sucks.
3582 ISD::CondCode LowCC;
3583 switch (CCCode) {
3584 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer setcc!");
3585 case ISD::SETLT:
3586 case ISD::SETULT: LowCC = ISD::SETULT; break;
3587 case ISD::SETGT:
3588 case ISD::SETUGT: LowCC = ISD::SETUGT; break;
3589 case ISD::SETLE:
3590 case ISD::SETULE: LowCC = ISD::SETULE; break;
3591 case ISD::SETGE:
3592 case ISD::SETUGE: LowCC = ISD::SETUGE; break;
3593 }
3594
3595 // LoCmp = lo(op1) < lo(op2) // Always unsigned comparison
3596 // HiCmp = hi(op1) < hi(op2) // Signedness depends on operands
3597 // dest = hi(op1) == hi(op2) ? LoCmp : HiCmp;
3598
3599 // NOTE: on targets without efficient SELECT of bools, we can always use
3600 // this identity: (B1 ? B2 : B3) --> (B1 & B2)|(!B1&B3)
3601 TargetLowering::DAGCombinerInfo DagCombineInfo(DAG, AfterLegalizeTypes, true,
3602 nullptr);
3603 SDValue LoCmp, HiCmp;
3604 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(LHSLo.getValueType()) &&
3605 TLI.isTypeLegal(RHSLo.getValueType()))
3606 LoCmp = TLI.SimplifySetCC(getSetCCResultType(LHSLo.getValueType()), LHSLo,
3607 RHSLo, LowCC, false, DagCombineInfo, dl);
3608 if (!LoCmp.getNode())
3609 LoCmp = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(LHSLo.getValueType()), LHSLo,
3610 RHSLo, LowCC);
3611 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(LHSHi.getValueType()) &&
3612 TLI.isTypeLegal(RHSHi.getValueType()))
3613 HiCmp = TLI.SimplifySetCC(getSetCCResultType(LHSHi.getValueType()), LHSHi,
3614 RHSHi, CCCode, false, DagCombineInfo, dl);
3615 if (!HiCmp.getNode())
3616 HiCmp =
3617 DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, getSetCCResultType(LHSHi.getValueType()),
3618 LHSHi, RHSHi, DAG.getCondCode(CCCode));
3619
3620 ConstantSDNode *LoCmpC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LoCmp.getNode());
3621 ConstantSDNode *HiCmpC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(HiCmp.getNode());
3622
3623 bool EqAllowed = (CCCode == ISD::SETLE || CCCode == ISD::SETGE ||
3624 CCCode == ISD::SETUGE || CCCode == ISD::SETULE);
3625
3626 if ((EqAllowed && (HiCmpC && HiCmpC->isNullValue())) ||
3627 (!EqAllowed && ((HiCmpC && (HiCmpC->getAPIntValue() == 1)) ||
3628 (LoCmpC && LoCmpC->isNullValue())))) {
3629 // For LE / GE, if high part is known false, ignore the low part.
3630 // For LT / GT: if low part is known false, return the high part.
3631 // if high part is known true, ignore the low part.
3632 NewLHS = HiCmp;
3633 NewRHS = SDValue();
3634 return;
3635 }
3636
3637 if (LHSHi == RHSHi) {
3638 // Comparing the low bits is enough.
3639 NewLHS = LoCmp;
3640 NewRHS = SDValue();
3641 return;
3642 }
3643
3644 // Lower with SETCCCARRY if the target supports it.
3645 EVT HiVT = LHSHi.getValueType();
3646 EVT ExpandVT = TLI.getTypeToExpandTo(*DAG.getContext(), HiVT);
3647 bool HasSETCCCARRY = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SETCCCARRY, ExpandVT);
3648
3649 // FIXME: Make all targets support this, then remove the other lowering.
3650 if (HasSETCCCARRY) {
3651 // SETCCCARRY can detect < and >= directly. For > and <=, flip
3652 // operands and condition code.
3653 bool FlipOperands = false;
3654 switch (CCCode) {
3655 case ISD::SETGT: CCCode = ISD::SETLT; FlipOperands = true; break;
3656 case ISD::SETUGT: CCCode = ISD::SETULT; FlipOperands = true; break;
3657 case ISD::SETLE: CCCode = ISD::SETGE; FlipOperands = true; break;
3658 case ISD::SETULE: CCCode = ISD::SETUGE; FlipOperands = true; break;
3659 default: break;
3660 }
3661 if (FlipOperands) {
3662 std::swap(LHSLo, RHSLo);
3663 std::swap(LHSHi, RHSHi);
3664 }
3665 // Perform a wide subtraction, feeding the carry from the low part into
3666 // SETCCCARRY. The SETCCCARRY operation is essentially looking at the high
3667 // part of the result of LHS - RHS. It is negative iff LHS < RHS. It is
3668 // zero or positive iff LHS >= RHS.
3669 EVT LoVT = LHSLo.getValueType();
3670 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(LoVT, getSetCCResultType(LoVT));
3671 SDValue LowCmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::USUBO, dl, VTList, LHSLo, RHSLo);
3672 SDValue Res = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCCCARRY, dl, getSetCCResultType(HiVT),
3673 LHSHi, RHSHi, LowCmp.getValue(1),
3674 DAG.getCondCode(CCCode));
3675 NewLHS = Res;
3676 NewRHS = SDValue();
3677 return;
3678 }
3679
3680 NewLHS = TLI.SimplifySetCC(getSetCCResultType(HiVT), LHSHi, RHSHi, ISD::SETEQ,
3681 false, DagCombineInfo, dl);
3682 if (!NewLHS.getNode())
3683 NewLHS =
3684 DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(HiVT), LHSHi, RHSHi, ISD::SETEQ);
3685 NewLHS = DAG.getSelect(dl, LoCmp.getValueType(), NewLHS, LoCmp, HiCmp);
3686 NewRHS = SDValue();
3687}
3688
3689SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_BR_CC(SDNode *N) {
3690 SDValue NewLHS = N->getOperand(2), NewRHS = N->getOperand(3);
3691 ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->get();
3692 IntegerExpandSetCCOperands(NewLHS, NewRHS, CCCode, SDLoc(N));
3693
3694 // If ExpandSetCCOperands returned a scalar, we need to compare the result
3695 // against zero to select between true and false values.
3696 if (!NewRHS.getNode()) {
3697 NewRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(N), NewLHS.getValueType());
3698 CCCode = ISD::SETNE;
3699 }
3700
3701 // Update N to have the operands specified.
3702 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0),
3703 DAG.getCondCode(CCCode), NewLHS, NewRHS,
3704 N->getOperand(4)), 0);
3705}
3706
3707SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_SELECT_CC(SDNode *N) {
3708 SDValue NewLHS = N->getOperand(0), NewRHS = N->getOperand(1);
3709 ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(4))->get();
3710 IntegerExpandSetCCOperands(NewLHS, NewRHS, CCCode, SDLoc(N));
3711
3712 // If ExpandSetCCOperands returned a scalar, we need to compare the result
3713 // against zero to select between true and false values.
3714 if (!NewRHS.getNode()) {
3715 NewRHS = DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(N), NewLHS.getValueType());
3716 CCCode = ISD::SETNE;
3717 }
3718
3719 // Update N to have the operands specified.
3720 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, NewLHS, NewRHS,
3721 N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3),
3722 DAG.getCondCode(CCCode)), 0);
3723}
3724
3725SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_SETCC(SDNode *N) {
3726 SDValue NewLHS = N->getOperand(0), NewRHS = N->getOperand(1);
3727 ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get();
3728 IntegerExpandSetCCOperands(NewLHS, NewRHS, CCCode, SDLoc(N));
3729
3730 // If ExpandSetCCOperands returned a scalar, use it.
3731 if (!NewRHS.getNode()) {
3732 assert(NewLHS.getValueType() == N->getValueType(0) &&
3733 "Unexpected setcc expansion!");
3734 return NewLHS;
3735 }
3736
3737 // Otherwise, update N to have the operands specified.
3738 return SDValue(
3739 DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, NewLHS, NewRHS, DAG.getCondCode(CCCode)), 0);
3740}

3742SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_SETCCCARRY(SDNode *N) {
3743 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
3744 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
3745 SDValue Carry = N->getOperand(2);
3746 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(3);
3747 SDLoc dl = SDLoc(N);
3748
3749 SDValue LHSLo, LHSHi, RHSLo, RHSHi;
3750 GetExpandedInteger(LHS, LHSLo, LHSHi);
3751 GetExpandedInteger(RHS, RHSLo, RHSHi);
3752
3753 // Expand to a SUBE for the low part and a smaller SETCCCARRY for the high.
3754 SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(LHSLo.getValueType(), Carry.getValueType());
3755 SDValue LowCmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBCARRY, dl, VTList, LHSLo, RHSLo, Carry);
3756 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCCCARRY, dl, N->getValueType(0), LHSHi, RHSHi,
3757 LowCmp.getValue(1), Cond);
3758}

3760SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_Shift(SDNode *N) {
3761 // The value being shifted is legal, but the shift amount is too big.
3762 // It follows that either the result of the shift is undefined, or the
3763 // upper half of the shift amount is zero. Just use the lower half.
3764 SDValue Lo, Hi;
3765 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(1), Lo, Hi);
3766 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, N->getOperand(0), Lo), 0);
3767}

3769SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_RETURNADDR(SDNode *N) {
3770 // The argument of RETURNADDR / FRAMEADDR builtin is 32 bit contant. This
3771 // surely makes pretty nice problems on 8/16 bit targets. Just truncate this
3772 // constant to valid type.
3773 SDValue Lo, Hi;
3774 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), Lo, Hi);
3775 return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, Lo), 0);
3776}

3778SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_SINT_TO_FP(SDNode *N) {
3779 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
3780 EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
3781 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getSINTTOFP(Op.getValueType(), DstVT);
3782 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL &&
3783 "Don't know how to expand this SINT_TO_FP!");
3784 return TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, DstVT, Op, true, SDLoc(N)).first;
3785}

3787SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_STORE(StoreSDNode *N, unsigned OpNo) {
3788 if (ISD::isNormalStore(N))
3789 return ExpandOp_NormalStore(N, OpNo);
3790
3791 assert(ISD::isUNINDEXEDStore(N) && "Indexed store during type legalization!");
3792 assert(OpNo == 1 && "Can only expand the stored value so far");
3793
3794 EVT VT = N->getOperand(1).getValueType();
3795 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
3796 SDValue Ch = N->getChain();
3797 SDValue Ptr = N->getBasePtr();
3798 unsigned Alignment = N->getAlignment();
3799 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = N->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
3800 AAMDNodes AAInfo = N->getAAInfo();
3801 SDLoc dl(N);
3802 SDValue Lo, Hi;
3803
3804 assert(NVT.isByteSized() && "Expanded type not byte sized!");
3805
3806 if (N->getMemoryVT().bitsLE(NVT)) {
3807 GetExpandedInteger(N->getValue(), Lo, Hi);
3808 return DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, dl, Lo, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(),
3809 N->getMemoryVT(), Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
3810 }
3811
3812 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) {
3813 // Little-endian - low bits are at low addresses.
3814 GetExpandedInteger(N->getValue(), Lo, Hi);
3815
3816 Lo = DAG.getStore(Ch, dl, Lo, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), Alignment, MMOFlags,
3817 AAInfo);
3818
3819 unsigned ExcessBits =
3820 N->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() - NVT.getSizeInBits();
3821 EVT NEVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExcessBits);
3822
3823 // Increment the pointer to the other half.
3824 unsigned IncrementSize = NVT.getSizeInBits()/8;
3825 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
3826 Hi = DAG.getTruncStore(
3827 Ch, dl, Hi, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), NEVT,
3828 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
3829 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
3830 }
3831
3832 // Big-endian - high bits are at low addresses. Favor aligned stores at
3833 // the cost of some bit-fiddling.
3834 GetExpandedInteger(N->getValue(), Lo, Hi);
3835
3836 EVT ExtVT = N->getMemoryVT();
3837 unsigned EBytes = ExtVT.getStoreSize();
3838 unsigned IncrementSize = NVT.getSizeInBits()/8;
3839 unsigned ExcessBits = (EBytes - IncrementSize)*8;
3840 EVT HiVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
3841 ExtVT.getSizeInBits() - ExcessBits);
3842
3843 if (ExcessBits < NVT.getSizeInBits()) {
3844 // Transfer high bits from the top of Lo to the bottom of Hi.
3845 Hi = DAG.getNode(
3846 ISD::SHL, dl, NVT, Hi,
3847 DAG.getConstant(NVT.getSizeInBits() - ExcessBits, dl,
3848 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
3849 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Hi,
3850 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, Lo,
3851 DAG.getConstant(ExcessBits, dl,
3852 TLI.getPointerRangeTy(
3853 DAG.getDataLayout()))));
3854 }
3855
3856 // Store both the high bits and maybe some of the low bits.
3857 Hi = DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, dl, Hi, Ptr, N->getPointerInfo(), HiVT, Alignment,
3858 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
3859
3860 // Increment the pointer to the other half.
3861 Ptr = DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
3862 // Store the lowest ExcessBits bits in the second half.
3863 Lo = DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, dl, Lo, Ptr,
3864 N->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
3865 EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExcessBits),
3866 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
3867 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
3868}
3869
3870SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_TRUNCATE(SDNode *N) {
3871 SDValue InL, InH;
3872 GetExpandedInteger(N->getOperand(0), InL, InH);
3873 // Just truncate the low part of the source.
3874 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), InL);
3875}

3877SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_UINT_TO_FP(SDNode *N) {
3878 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
3879 EVT SrcVT = Op.getValueType();
3880 EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
3881 SDLoc dl(N);
3882
3883 // The following optimization is valid only if every value in SrcVT (when
3884 // treated as signed) is representable in DstVT. Check that the mantissa
3885 // size of DstVT is >= than the number of bits in SrcVT -1.
3886 const fltSemantics &sem = DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(DstVT);
3887 if (APFloat::semanticsPrecision(sem) >= SrcVT.getSizeInBits()-1 &&
3888 TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, SrcVT) == TargetLowering::Custom){
3889 // Do a signed conversion then adjust the result.
3890 SDValue SignedConv = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DstVT, Op);
3891 SignedConv = TLI.LowerOperation(SignedConv, DAG);
3892
3893 // The result of the signed conversion needs adjusting if the 'sign bit' of
3894 // the incoming integer was set. To handle this, we dynamically test to see
3895 // if it is set, and, if so, add a fudge factor.
3896
3897 const uint64_t F32TwoE32 = 0x4F800000ULL;
3898 const uint64_t F32TwoE64 = 0x5F800000ULL;
3899 const uint64_t F32TwoE128 = 0x7F800000ULL;
3900
3901 APInt FF(32, 0);
3902 if (SrcVT == MVT::i32)
3903 FF = APInt(32, F32TwoE32);
3904 else if (SrcVT == MVT::i64)
3905 FF = APInt(32, F32TwoE64);
3906 else if (SrcVT == MVT::i128)
3907 FF = APInt(32, F32TwoE128);
3908 else
3909 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported UINT_TO_FP!");
3910
3911 // Check whether the sign bit is set.
3912 SDValue Lo, Hi;
3913 GetExpandedInteger(Op, Lo, Hi);
3914 SDValue SignSet = DAG.getSetCC(dl,
3915 getSetCCResultType(Hi.getValueType()),
3916 Hi,
3917 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Hi.getValueType()),
3918 ISD::SETLT);
3919
3920 // Build a 64 bit pair (0, FF) in the constant pool, with FF in the lo bits.
3921 SDValue FudgePtr = DAG.getConstantPool(
3922 ConstantInt::get(*DAG.getContext(), FF.zext(64)),
3923 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
3924 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
3925
3926 // Get a pointer to FF if the sign bit was set, or to 0 otherwise.
3927 SDValue Zero = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl);
3928 SDValue Four = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(4, dl);
3929 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
3930 std::swap(Zero, Four);
3931 SDValue Offset = DAG.getSelect(dl, Zero.getValueType(), SignSet,
3932 Zero, Four);
3933 unsigned Alignment = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(FudgePtr)->getAlignment();
3934 FudgePtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, FudgePtr.getValueType(),
3935 FudgePtr, Offset);
3936 Alignment = std::min(Alignment, 4u);
3937
3938 // Load the value out, extending it from f32 to the destination float type.
3939 // FIXME: Avoid the extend by constructing the right constant pool?
3940 SDValue Fudge = DAG.getExtLoad(
3941 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, DstVT, DAG.getEntryNode(), FudgePtr,
3942 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MVT::f32,
3943 Alignment);
3944 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DstVT, SignedConv, Fudge);
3945 }
3946
3947 // Otherwise, use a libcall.
3948 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getUINTTOFP(SrcVT, DstVT);
3949 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL &&
3950 "Don't know how to expand this UINT_TO_FP!");
3951 return TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, DstVT, Op, true, dl).first;
3952}

3954SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntOp_ATOMIC_STORE(SDNode *N) {
3955 SDLoc dl(N);
3956 SDValue Swap = DAG.getAtomic(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, dl,
3957 cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getMemoryVT(),
3958 N->getOperand(0),
3959 N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2),
3960 cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand());
3961 return Swap.getValue(1);
3962}

3965SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(SDNode *N) {
3966
3967 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
3968 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
3969 assert(NOutVT.isVector() && "This type must be promoted to a vector type");
3970 unsigned OutNumElems = OutVT.getVectorNumElements();
3971 EVT NOutVTElem = NOutVT.getVectorElementType();
3972
3973 SDLoc dl(N);
3974 SDValue BaseIdx = N->getOperand(1);
3975
3976 SDValue InOp0 = N->getOperand(0);
3977 if (getTypeAction(InOp0.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger)
3978 InOp0 = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
3979
3980 EVT InVT = InOp0.getValueType();
3981
3982 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
3983 Ops.reserve(OutNumElems);
3984 for (unsigned i = 0; i != OutNumElems; ++i) {
3985
3986 // Extract the element from the original vector.
3987 SDValue Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, BaseIdx.getValueType(),
3988 BaseIdx, DAG.getConstant(i, dl, BaseIdx.getValueType()));
3989 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl,
3990 InVT.getVectorElementType(), N->getOperand(0), Index);
3991
3992 SDValue Op = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Ext, dl, NOutVTElem);
3993 // Insert the converted element to the new vector.
3994 Ops.push_back(Op);
3995 }
3996
3997 return DAG.getBuildVector(NOutVT, dl, Ops);
3998}

4016SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_BUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
4017 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
4018 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
4019 assert(NOutVT.isVector() && "This type must be promoted to a vector type");
4020 unsigned NumElems = N->getNumOperands();
4021 EVT NOutVTElem = NOutVT.getVectorElementType();
4022
4023 SDLoc dl(N);
4024
4025 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
4026 Ops.reserve(NumElems);
4027 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElems; ++i) {
4028 SDValue Op;
4029 // BUILD_VECTOR integer operand types are allowed to be larger than the
4030 // result's element type. This may still be true after the promotion. For
4031 // example, we might be promoting (<v?i1> = BV <i32>, <i32>, ...) to
4032 // (v?i16 = BV <i32>, <i32>, ...), and we can't any_extend <i32> to <i16>.
4033 if (N->getOperand(i).getValueType().bitsLT(NOutVTElem))
4034 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVTElem, N->getOperand(i));
4035 else
4036 Op = N->getOperand(i);
4037 Ops.push_back(Op);
4038 }
4039
4040 return DAG.getBuildVector(NOutVT, dl, Ops);
4041}

4043SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_SCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDNode *N) {
4044
4045 SDLoc dl(N);
4046
4047 assert(!N->getOperand(0).getValueType().isVector() &&
4048 "Input must be a scalar");
4049

4051 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
4052 assert(NOutVT.isVector() && "This type must be promoted to a vector type");
4053 EVT NOutVTElem = NOutVT.getVectorElementType();
4054
4055 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NOutVTElem, N->getOperand(0));

4060SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
4061 SDLoc dl(N);
4062
4063 EVT OutVT = N->getValueType(0);
4064 EVT NOutVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), OutVT);
4065 assert(NOutVT.isVector() && "This type must be promoted to a vector type");
4066
4067 EVT OutElemTy = NOutVT.getVectorElementType();
4068
4069 unsigned NumElem = N->getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
4070 unsigned NumOutElem = NOutVT.getVectorNumElements();
4071 unsigned NumOperands = N->getNumOperands();
4072 assert(NumElem * NumOperands == NumOutElem &&
4073 "Unexpected number of elements");
4074
4075 // Take the elements from the first vector.
4076 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops(NumOutElem);
4077 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumOperands; ++i) {
4078 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(i);
4079 if (getTypeAction(Op.getValueType()) == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger)
4080 Op = GetPromotedInteger(Op);
4081 EVT SclrTy = Op.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
4082 assert(NumElem == Op.getValueType().getVectorNumElements() &&
4083 "Unexpected number of elements");
4084
4085 for (unsigned j = 0; j < NumElem; ++j) {
4086 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(
4087 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, SclrTy, Op,
4088 DAG.getConstant(j, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4089 Ops[i * NumElem + j] = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Ext, dl, OutElemTy);
4090 }
4091 }
4092
4093 return DAG.getBuildVector(NOutVT, dl, Ops);
4094}

4096SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntRes_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG(SDNode *N) {
4097 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4098 EVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), VT);
4099 assert(NVT.isVector() && "This type must be promoted to a vector type");
4100
4101 SDLoc dl(N);
4102
4103 // For operands whose TypeAction is to promote, extend the promoted node
4104 // appropriately (ZERO_EXTEND or SIGN_EXTEND) from the original pre-promotion
4105 // type, and then construct a new *_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG node to the promote-to
4106 // type..
4107 if (getTypeAction(N->getOperand(0).getValueType())
4108 == TargetLowering::TypePromoteInteger) {
4109 SDValue Promoted;
4110
4111 switch(N->getOpcode()) {
4112 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
4113 Promoted = SExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
4114 break;
4115 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
4116 Promoted = ZExtPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
4117 break;
4118 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG:
4119 Promoted = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
4120 break;
4121 default:
4122 llvm_unreachable("Node has unexpected Opcode");
4123 }
4124 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Promoted);
4125 }
4126
4127 // Directly extend to the appropriate transform-to type.
4128 return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, N->getOperand(0));
4129}

4155SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDNode *N) {
4156 SDLoc dl(N);
4157 SDValue V0 = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(0));
4158 SDValue V1 = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(N->getOperand(1), dl,
4159 TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout()));
4160 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl,
4161 V0->getValueType(0).getScalarType(), V0, V1);
4162
4163 // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT can return types which are wider than the incoming
4164 // element types. If this is the case then we need to expand the outgoing
4165 // value and not truncate it.
4166 return DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Ext, dl, N->getValueType(0));
4167}

4179SDValue DAGTypeLegalizer::PromoteIntOp_CONCAT_VECTORS(SDNode *N) {
4180 SDLoc dl(N);
4181 unsigned NumElems = N->getNumOperands();
4182
4183 EVT RetSclrTy = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
4184
4185 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewOps;
4186 NewOps.reserve(NumElems);
4187
4188 // For each incoming vector
4189 for (unsigned VecIdx = 0; VecIdx != NumElems; ++VecIdx) {
4190 SDValue Incoming = GetPromotedInteger(N->getOperand(VecIdx));
4191 EVT SclrTy = Incoming->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType();
4192 unsigned NumElem = Incoming->getValueType(0).getVectorNumElements();
4193
4194 for (unsigned i=0; i<NumElem; ++i) {
4195 // Extract element from incoming vector
4196 SDValue Ex = DAG.getNode(
4197 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, SclrTy, Incoming,
4198 DAG.getConstant(i, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
4199 SDValue Tr = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, RetSclrTy, Ex);
4200 NewOps.push_back(Tr);
4201 }
4202 }
4203
4204 return DAG.getBuildVector(N->getValueType(0), dl, NewOps);
4205}
